<img alt="Tiff in Tech 使用 Palali Music 的 sonido original 创作的 Learning about this blew my mind. There is a lot more information on ICANN on their blog! Also, although we are referencing “7 people” in the video, that is a reference often used but it is much more complicated.. here is a snippet from their website..  There are around fifty different experts who are directly involved in key ceremonies. Twenty-one of these are selected from the global Internet community. They are divided into three groups of seven people. Each group has a different purpose. Because we need people from these groups to participate in key ceremonies as part of the security protection for the key signing key, it is often simplified to the idea that there are seven keys to the Internet, or there are seven people that control the Internet. This, however, masks the true complexity that involves many levels of overlapping controls. The complete design requires far more than seven individuals or seven keys to access or use the root zone key signing key. #tech #technology #stem #techexplained " fetchpriority="auto" decoding="async" src="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/o06DnQ6IAyGfAQOIWILdAfDGAAkBAFh1efhRlJ?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=CAvX04Z5fE3cnWue8FQET1%2BXPxs%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=-" imagex-type="react" imagex-version="0.3.10" srcset="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/o06DnQ6IAyGfAQOIWILdAfDGAAkBAFh1efhRlJ?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=CAvX04Z5fE3cnWue8FQET1%2BXPxs%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 1x, https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/o06DnQ6IAyGfAQOIWILdAfDGAAkBAFh1efhRlJ?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=CAvX04Z5fE3cnWue8FQET1%2BXPxs%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 2x" style="position: absolute; inset: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0px; border: none; margin: auto; display: block; width: 0px; height: 0px; min-width: 100%; max-width: 100%; min-height: 100%; max-height: 100%;">

<img alt="Tiff in Tech 使用 Melodality 的 Artificial Intelligence 创作的 The most inefficient design in modern technology is sitting right in front of you. It's your keyboard and there is a really interesting reason why we can't get rid of it. In the 1870s, early typewriters had a serious problem. When people typed too quickly, the mechanical arms would crash into each other and jam. The solution? Keyboard designer Christopher Sholes rearranged the letters to put commonly used pairs far apart. Some people say the QWERTY layout already existed and was invented by telegram operators. But you can decide that. Regardless, this design helped slow typing down.  Think about it: 'E' and 'R' are typed with different fingers. 'T' and 'H' are on opposite sides. This isn't random - it's intentionally inefficient to prevent those mechanical jams. When computers came along, we no longer needed this slow-down design. We could arrange letters any way we wanted. In fact, in 1936, August Dvorak created a scientifically optimized keyboard layout that was 74% more efficient. But by then, millions of people had already learned QWERTY. The inefficient design had won. #tech #technology #coding #stem #techexplained " fetchpriority="auto" decoding="async" src="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/ognXBfx4IAOSC2yEEmAc4BAEARFOaJfxMQLDDE?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=8hPbVxU%2BDrJR%2B0uBxGSDjLrMKtY%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=-" imagex-type="react" imagex-version="0.3.10" srcset="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/ognXBfx4IAOSC2yEEmAc4BAEARFOaJfxMQLDDE?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=8hPbVxU%2BDrJR%2B0uBxGSDjLrMKtY%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 1x, https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/ognXBfx4IAOSC2yEEmAc4BAEARFOaJfxMQLDDE?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=8hPbVxU%2BDrJR%2B0uBxGSDjLrMKtY%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 2x" style="position: absolute; inset: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0px; border: none; margin: auto; display: block; width: 0px; height: 0px; min-width: 100%; max-width: 100%; min-height: 100%; max-height: 100%;">

<img alt="Tiff in Tech 使用 Melodality 的 Artificial Intelligence 创作的 Google's quantum computer did something that would take our fastest supercomputers 10 SEPTILLION years... in just five minutes! Let me break down how that's even possible. Our normal computers, work with bits - basically tiny switches that are either ON or OFF. That's it. Just 1s and 0s. Let's say you wanted to crack a password with 10 characters. A regular computer would have to try each combination one at a time - that could take years! But a quantum computer? It could try all possible combinations simultaneously. It's like having millions of computers working in parallel! This is possible because quantum computers use qubits, which can be ON and OFF at the same time. I know, I know. How is that possible? Well, this is where things get REALLY interesting. Researchers use individual atoms, super-cooled to near absolute zero - that's colder than space itself! At these temperatures, atoms start behaving according to quantum mechanics, where the normal rules of physics just... don't apply. But here's the catch - it's INCREDIBLY difficult to maintain this quantum state. Think about trying to balance a pencil on its tip... while riding a bicycle... during an earthquake. That's STILL easier than keeping qubits stable! Scientists call this problem &quot;decoherence. &quot; Right now, the best quantum computers have about 100 working qubits. But here's something wild - a quantum computer with just 300 qubits would be able to perform more simultaneous calculations than there are atoms in the observable universe! And the coolest part? We're just scratching the surface. #tech #technology #stem #techexplained #quantumphysics #quantumcomputing " fetchpriority="auto" decoding="async" src="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/o07GLEfiZI4A9CVxIAAUIecPSls7OQADMC8jge?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=6G8cGdNAE%2FcGOXcjfZGII8Fd2nw%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=-" imagex-type="react" imagex-version="0.3.10" srcset="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/o07GLEfiZI4A9CVxIAAUIecPSls7OQADMC8jge?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=6G8cGdNAE%2FcGOXcjfZGII8Fd2nw%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 1x, https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/o07GLEfiZI4A9CVxIAAUIecPSls7OQADMC8jge?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=6G8cGdNAE%2FcGOXcjfZGII8Fd2nw%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 2x" style="position: absolute; inset: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0px; border: none; margin: auto; display: block; width: 0px; height: 0px; min-width: 100%; max-width: 100%; min-height: 100%; max-height: 100%;">

<img alt="Tiff in Tech 使用 Palali Music 的 sonido original 创作的 Meta might be about to make one of the most important infrastructure moves in internet history, for $10 billion, and most people have no idea it's happening. They're potentially planning a massive underwater internet cable that'll wrap around the world like this, connecting the US, South Africa, India, and Australia. But here's why this is such a big deal: Remember how your parents taught you not to put all your eggs in one basket? Well, right now, the internet's eggs are mostly in some pretty risky baskets. See, crucial internet cables keep getting cut in conflict zones like the Red Sea. When that happens, millions lose reliable internet access. Meta's new route? It completely avoids these hotspots. Think about it - Meta handles 22% of all mobile internet traffic. That's billions of WhatsApp messages, Instagram reels, and Facebook posts. And with AI coming into play, they need even more bandwidth. This isn't just about Meta building a fancy new cable. It's about rewiring the internet's backbone to be more secure, more reliable, and ready for whatever comes next. The future of our connection to each other is being built right under our oceans. And now you know why it matters.  #tech #technology #techexplained #stem " fetchpriority="auto" decoding="async" src="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/tos-maliva-p-0068/oEfOkEj6InDnCcfEPYFfMQ6RC0kZQgCjFXES0A~tplv-dmt-logom:tos-useast2a-v-0068/oMAgAIHOVhzIfB3A4BBxnECEEpMIihioA4MCHd.image?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=RvdxiqijXzquDBtXKbPFmLNWxNo%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=-" imagex-type="react" imagex-version="0.3.10" srcset="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/tos-maliva-p-0068/oEfOkEj6InDnCcfEPYFfMQ6RC0kZQgCjFXES0A~tplv-dmt-logom:tos-useast2a-v-0068/oMAgAIHOVhzIfB3A4BBxnECEEpMIihioA4MCHd.image?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=RvdxiqijXzquDBtXKbPFmLNWxNo%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 1x, https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/tos-maliva-p-0068/oEfOkEj6InDnCcfEPYFfMQ6RC0kZQgCjFXES0A~tplv-dmt-logom:tos-useast2a-v-0068/oMAgAIHOVhzIfB3A4BBxnECEEpMIihioA4MCHd.image?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=RvdxiqijXzquDBtXKbPFmLNWxNo%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 2x" style="position: absolute; inset: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0px; border: none; margin: auto; display: block; width: 0px; height: 0px; min-width: 100%; max-width: 100%; min-height: 100%; max-height: 100%;">

<img alt="Tiff in Tech 使用 Tiff in Tech 的 original sound 创作的 Are self driving cars really safer than when humans drive? Heres how they work technically so you can decide.  Self-driving cars work by using multiple sensors (cameras, radar, and LiDAR) to create a 360-degree view of their surroundings. These sensors act like the car's eyes and ears, constantly collecting data about nearby objects, road conditions, and traffic. A powerful computer system processes this information using artificial intelligence to understand what everything is (like pedestrians, other cars, or road signs) and predict how they might move. The AI then makes decisions about steering, braking, and acceleration - just like a human driver would, but using precise calculations. The system constantly learns from its experiences and updates its decision-making to handle new situations better. #tech #technology #coding #stem #techexplained " fetchpriority="auto" decoding="async" src="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/tos-maliva-p-0068/a8f51b0e5d4749cc9800a10a2444f613_1729816555~tplv-dmt-logom:tos-useast2a-v-0068/oYAfISEDA1fCF9cAzOc1IloQeAFlCjANZnERPg.image?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=Tx9tfuHIJWwyJmW4HXhC%2FiOEZt8%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=-" imagex-type="react" imagex-version="0.3.10" srcset="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/tos-maliva-p-0068/a8f51b0e5d4749cc9800a10a2444f613_1729816555~tplv-dmt-logom:tos-useast2a-v-0068/oYAfISEDA1fCF9cAzOc1IloQeAFlCjANZnERPg.image?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=Tx9tfuHIJWwyJmW4HXhC%2FiOEZt8%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 1x, https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/tos-maliva-p-0068/a8f51b0e5d4749cc9800a10a2444f613_1729816555~tplv-dmt-logom:tos-useast2a-v-0068/oYAfISEDA1fCF9cAzOc1IloQeAFlCjANZnERPg.image?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=Tx9tfuHIJWwyJmW4HXhC%2FiOEZt8%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 2x" style="position: absolute; inset: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0px; border: none; margin: auto; display: block; width: 0px; height: 0px; min-width: 100%; max-width: 100%; min-height: 100%; max-height: 100%;">

<img alt="Tiff in Tech 使用 Tiff in Tech 的 original sound 创作的 What is the difference between Python and JavaScript?!  JavaScript and Python serve different main purposes - JavaScript was designed to make websites interactive and runs primarily in web browsers, while Python is a general-purpose language used for various tasks like data analysis, AI, and running programs on computers. Python is often easier to learn due to its simpler commands and comes with many built-in tools, while JavaScript is more flexible but typically focused on web development.  #tech #technology #coding #stem #techexplained " fetchpriority="auto" decoding="async" src="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/700ee308c7304ffe94c51b8e94e56010_1729816519?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=ZgXjLU0P7JFF6UdNGEM8zDV2t0I%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=-" imagex-type="react" imagex-version="0.3.10" srcset="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/700ee308c7304ffe94c51b8e94e56010_1729816519?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=ZgXjLU0P7JFF6UdNGEM8zDV2t0I%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 1x, https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/700ee308c7304ffe94c51b8e94e56010_1729816519?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=ZgXjLU0P7JFF6UdNGEM8zDV2t0I%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 2x" style="position: absolute; inset: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0px; border: none; margin: auto; display: block; width: 0px; height: 0px; min-width: 100%; max-width: 100%; min-height: 100%; max-height: 100%;">

<img alt="Tiff in Tech 使用 Tiff in Tech 的 original sound 创作的 How secure are password managers... really? Password managers store your login credentials in an encrypted vault. They work by: - Using a master password to generate a strong encryption key - Encrypting each password locally on your device - Storing the encrypted data locally or in the cloud - Decrypting passwords only when needed, using your master password To stay secure: -Create a strong master password (16+ characters, mix of characters) -Enable two-factor authentication with an authenticator app -Keep your devices and software updated -Set auto-lock timers and make regular backups -Watch for suspicious login attempts or sync errors #tech #technology #coding #strm #techexplained #techexpert " fetchpriority="auto" decoding="async" src="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/okIii9QgSeALcIjPwyjQZMeietGnCC8gPFMOFy?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=OUgy0Zj8JDi7EdVKcthylri%2FGVw%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=-" imagex-type="react" imagex-version="0.3.10" srcset="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/okIii9QgSeALcIjPwyjQZMeietGnCC8gPFMOFy?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=OUgy0Zj8JDi7EdVKcthylri%2FGVw%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 1x, https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/okIii9QgSeALcIjPwyjQZMeietGnCC8gPFMOFy?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=OUgy0Zj8JDi7EdVKcthylri%2FGVw%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 2x" style="position: absolute; inset: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0px; border: none; margin: auto; display: block; width: 0px; height: 0px; min-width: 100%; max-width: 100%; min-height: 100%; max-height: 100%;">

<img alt="Tiff in Tech 使用 Palali Music 的 sonido original 创作的 RAM (Random Access Memory) is like a chef's workspace in a kitchen. It provides quick-access temporary storage for data that the computer's processor (the chef) needs to work with immediately. Just as a larger countertop allows a chef to handle more ingredients and tasks at once, more RAM enables a computer to run more programs simultaneously or handle larger files. When you turn off your computer, the RAM clears, similar to how a chef cleans their workspace after finishing. This temporary, fast-access nature of RAM is crucial for a computer's smooth operation, especially when multitasking. #tech #technology #stem #techexplained " fetchpriority="auto" src="data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAIBRAA7" imagex-type="react" imagex-version="0.3.10" style="position: absolute; inset: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0px; border: none; margin: auto; display: block; width: 0px; height: 0px; min-width: 100%; max-width: 100%; min-height: 100%; max-height: 100%;">

<img alt="Tiff in Tech 使用 Tiff in Tech 的 original sound 创作的 Save for your next tech interview 💡 What happens when you type a URL into a browser?! First, the browser checks its cache for a stored version of the site. If not found, it contacts a Domain Name System (DNS) server to translate the domain name into an IP address. Using this IP address, the browser establishes a connection with the web server hosting the site through a protocol called TCP/IP. It then sends an HTTP request asking for the specific page. The server processes this request and sends back the necessary files (HTML, CSS, JavaScript, images, etc.) in an HTTP response. Finally, the browser renders these files, executing any scripts and applying styles to display the web page on your screen. #tech #technology #coding #stem #techexplained " fetchpriority="auto" src="data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAIBRAA7" imagex-type="react" imagex-version="0.3.10" style="position: absolute; inset: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0px; border: none; margin: auto; display: block; width: 0px; height: 0px; min-width: 100%; max-width: 100%; min-height: 100%; max-height: 100%;">
https://www.tiktok.com/@tiffintech/video/7424655194488638726
<img alt="Tiff in Tech 使用 Tiff in Tech 的 original sound 创作的 What ia the difference between serverless computing and containers?! Serverless, managed by cloud providers, allows developers to focus on code, scales automatically, and charges only for compute time used. It's ideal for intermittent workloads but can face latency issues. Containers offer more control, run continuously, and suit complex applications better. A real-world example: A retail website might use serverless functions for product page views during a flash sale, scaling instantly to meet demand. Meanwhile, the persistent inventory management system could run in containers, maintaining constant uptime and state. This hybrid approach capitalizes on serverless for sporadic high traffic and containers for consistent, complex operations. #tech #technology #techexplained #stem " fetchpriority="auto" src="data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAIBRAA7" imagex-type="react" imagex-version="0.3.10" style="position: absolute; inset: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0px; border: none; margin: auto; display: block; width: 0px; height: 0px; min-width: 100%; max-width: 100%; min-height: 100%; max-height: 100%;">
https://www.tiktok.com/@tiffintech/video/7424225781443841285
<img alt="Tiff in Tech 使用 Tiff in Tech 的 original sound 创作的 What exactly is DNS? This is something you might hear often in a tech interview or at a company you're working for. You can think of DNS like a phone book before the Internet. Just as you would use a phone book. Okay. Well, maybe we don't use phone books anymore. Our parents would use phone books to look up someone's name and phone number in the phone book. DNS helps your computer find the right website based on its domain name. When you type in. I love dogs. I mean, I know dogs are better than cats, let's face it. But regardless, when you type it in, computer doesn't actually know where to find. I love dogs dot com. It needs to translate this domain into an IP address, which is a unique numerical label that is assigned to each device connected to the internet. That's where DNS comes in. Your computer will send a request to the DNS server asking for the IP address of Isle of Dogs dot com, and the DNS server will respond with the correct IP address allowing your computer to connect to Isle of Dogs dot com website. And this process happens every single time you type in a website you want to visit. Save for your next tech interview.  #tech #stem #technology #techexplained " fetchpriority="auto" decoding="async" src="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/fc0d2d3b324e46b5a299d9f94fa79d52_1728587275?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=XSkM2sNzDtAIHnLSSv7vjAUk5Fc%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=-" imagex-type="react" imagex-version="0.3.10" srcset="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/fc0d2d3b324e46b5a299d9f94fa79d52_1728587275?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=XSkM2sNzDtAIHnLSSv7vjAUk5Fc%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 1x, https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/fc0d2d3b324e46b5a299d9f94fa79d52_1728587275?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=XSkM2sNzDtAIHnLSSv7vjAUk5Fc%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 2x" style="position: absolute; inset: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0px; border: none; margin: auto; display: block; width: 0px; height: 0px; min-width: 100%; max-width: 100%; min-height: 100%; max-height: 100%;">

<img alt="Tiff in Tech 使用 Tiff in Tech 的 original sound 创作的 The fact that humans invented all of this will forever blow my mind.  How do computers understand so many different programming languages?  Computers only truly understand machine code - instructions in 1s and 0s. Programming languages are tools that make it easier for humans to write instructions for computers. These languages work because: Translator programs convert human-friendly code into machine code. Languages have clear rules for how they should be translated. Computers are built to recognize common programming patterns. Some languages use helper systems to manage the translation process. It's like having a friend who seems to understand many languages, but is actually translating everything to their native tongue in their head. Similarly, computers appear to understand various programming languages, but are really just processing everything into their native binary language. #tech #technology #coding #stem #developer #computerscience #compsci " fetchpriority="auto" decoding="async" src="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/316f09d8f4054c2a9e5458ac99d2782f_1728503905?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=Q%2Fs2Bf2%2BxSNhQMe%2F09%2FzRVKbs8w%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=-" imagex-type="react" imagex-version="0.3.10" srcset="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/316f09d8f4054c2a9e5458ac99d2782f_1728503905?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=Q%2Fs2Bf2%2BxSNhQMe%2F09%2FzRVKbs8w%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 1x, https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/316f09d8f4054c2a9e5458ac99d2782f_1728503905?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=Q%2Fs2Bf2%2BxSNhQMe%2F09%2FzRVKbs8w%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 2x" style="position: absolute; inset: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0px; border: none; margin: auto; display: block; width: 0px; height: 0px; min-width: 100%; max-width: 100%; min-height: 100%; max-height: 100%;">

<img alt="Tiff in Tech 使用 Tiff in Tech 的 original sound 创作的 What is the difference between JavaScript vs Typescript?!  JavaScript and TypeScript are both programming languages used for web development, with TypeScript being a superset of JavaScript that adds optional static typing. While JavaScript is dynamic and flexible, allowing for quick development but potentially leading to runtime errors, TypeScript introduces static typing and compile-time checks. This helps catch errors earlier in the development process and can lead to more robust, maintainable code, especially in larger projects. TypeScript also offers better IDE support and enhanced object-oriented programming features. However, it comes with a steeper learning curve and requires a compilation step. JavaScript remains popular for its simplicity and is often preferred for smaller projects or rapid prototyping. #tech #technology #stem #developer " fetchpriority="auto" decoding="async" src="https://p16-sign-sg.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-alisg-p-0037/54950b56786a44c7a82baebf2916ea63_1727193326?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=eyJjz1QjeyOWgxb9xRM%2BGll8A5k%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=-" imagex-type="react" imagex-version="0.3.10" srcset="https://p16-sign-sg.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-alisg-p-0037/54950b56786a44c7a82baebf2916ea63_1727193326?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=eyJjz1QjeyOWgxb9xRM%2BGll8A5k%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 1x, https://p16-sign-sg.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-alisg-p-0037/54950b56786a44c7a82baebf2916ea63_1727193326?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=eyJjz1QjeyOWgxb9xRM%2BGll8A5k%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 2x" style="position: absolute; inset: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0px; border: none; margin: auto; display: block; width: 0px; height: 0px; min-width: 100%; max-width: 100%; min-height: 100%; max-height: 100%;">

<img alt="Tiff in Tech 使用 Palali Music 的 sonido original 创作的 What is quantum computing? In simple terms  Classical Computing: Uses bits - basic units of information that can be either 0 or 1 Processes information sequentially Best for everyday tasks like word processing, web browsing, etc. Quantum Computing: Uses qubits - can be 0, 1, or both simultaneously (superposition) Can process multiple possibilities at once Excels at specific complex problems like cryptography and molecular modeling The main advantage of quantum computing is its ability to perform certain calculations much faster than classical computers for particular types of problems. However, quantum computers are still in early stages of development and aren't yet practical for most everyday computing tasks. #tech #technology #coding #stem " fetchpriority="auto" decoding="async" src="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/oMi3n1YiZsuudGZBESJUCyPj4kIBB3QtmdEMA?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=nWbyg4hxqfS%2BC9k1iL0kMfAGFA4%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=-" imagex-type="react" imagex-version="0.3.10" srcset="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/oMi3n1YiZsuudGZBESJUCyPj4kIBB3QtmdEMA?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=nWbyg4hxqfS%2BC9k1iL0kMfAGFA4%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 1x, https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/oMi3n1YiZsuudGZBESJUCyPj4kIBB3QtmdEMA?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=nWbyg4hxqfS%2BC9k1iL0kMfAGFA4%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 2x" style="position: absolute; inset: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0px; border: none; margin: auto; display: block; width: 0px; height: 0px; min-width: 100%; max-width: 100%; min-height: 100%; max-height: 100%;">

<img alt="Tiff in Tech 使用 Outkast 的 Ms. Jackson (Instrumental) 创作的 What is the difference between GraphQL vs. REST? REST APIs are like traditional restaurant ordering, requiring multiple specific requests for different pieces of information, potentially over-delivering data, and needing menu updates for changes. In contrast, GraphQL is akin to a customizable ordering system, allowing a single request to fetch precisely the desired data, offering greater flexibility, and easily accommodating new options without overhauling the entire system. In essence, REST is like ordering from a traditional menu with set meals, while GraphQL is like having a fully customizable ordering system where you specify exactly what you want in one go.  #tech #technology #coding #stem " fetchpriority="auto" decoding="async" src="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/eab2772fb244406aa4f711fd7e9b83ca_1726854759?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=DmrZt4y3L%2BX%2FssURfPMJUO%2Fic%2B4%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=-" imagex-type="react" imagex-version="0.3.10" srcset="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/eab2772fb244406aa4f711fd7e9b83ca_1726854759?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=DmrZt4y3L%2BX%2FssURfPMJUO%2Fic%2B4%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 1x, https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/eab2772fb244406aa4f711fd7e9b83ca_1726854759?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=DmrZt4y3L%2BX%2FssURfPMJUO%2Fic%2B4%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 2x" style="position: absolute; inset: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0px; border: none; margin: auto; display: block; width: 0px; height: 0px; min-width: 100%; max-width: 100%; min-height: 100%; max-height: 100%;">

<img alt="Tiff in Tech 使用 Outkast 的 Ms. Jackson (Instrumental) 创作的 Imagine a world without this invention?!😅 This is Douglas Engelbart. And he solved a massive problem that we faced with computers.  Back in the 1960s, computers were massive, intimidating machines operated by punch cards and keyboards. Douglas envisioned a more seamless way to interact with them.  Therefore, he and his team at Stanford began experimenting with various pointing devices, including a knee-operated pointer and a stylus. BUT these early attempts were impractical for everyday use. Engelbart persisted, eventually crafting a wooden shell housing two metal wheels. BUT at the time, most people interacted with computers through complex command-line interfaces or punch card systems. The mouse remained largely unknown outside of research circles for years. BUT as personal computers began to emerge in the late 1970s, the need for user-friendly interfaces became apparent. THEREFORE, companies like Apple began to take notice of Engelbart's invention. BUT it wasn't until 1984, with the release of the Apple Macintosh, that the mouse finally found its way into the hands of everyday users. Engelbart's perseverance and vision ultimately transformed how we interact with computers, even if it took nearly two decades for his invention to achieve widespread recognition and use. Share this with a tech enthusiast 💡 #tech #technology #techexplainer #techexplained " fetchpriority="auto" decoding="async" src="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/226ed233040545ada802692b28243235_1726757802?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=KGS6tmsUWcZUAuI12lRJYzqsYLc%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=-" imagex-type="react" imagex-version="0.3.10" srcset="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/226ed233040545ada802692b28243235_1726757802?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=KGS6tmsUWcZUAuI12lRJYzqsYLc%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 1x, https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/226ed233040545ada802692b28243235_1726757802?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=KGS6tmsUWcZUAuI12lRJYzqsYLc%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 2x" style="position: absolute; inset: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0px; border: none; margin: auto; display: block; width: 0px; height: 0px; min-width: 100%; max-width: 100%; min-height: 100%; max-height: 100%;">

<img alt="Tiff in Tech 使用 Palali Music 的 sonido original 创作的 What is the difference between Docker and Virtual Machines?  Virtual machines and Docker are both technologies used to run applications in isolated environments, but they work differently. A virtual machine (VM) is like a complete computer running inside your actual computer. It has its own operating system and uses a portion of your computer's resources to run as if it were a separate machine. Docker, on the other hand, uses containers. These containers share the host computer's operating system kernel but are isolated from each other. They're lighter and faster to start up than VMs because they don't need a full OS for each application. Think of VMs as separate apartments in a building, each with its own utilities, while Docker containers are more like efficient, self-contained rooms that share the building's main systems. #tech #technology #techexplained #stem #developer " fetchpriority="auto" decoding="async" src="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/ecdc11149f4a4ecb89a6556b4674859f_1726505694?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=IXb03DcV3sEg0X%2B5Sxt2FX6%2B4C8%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=-" imagex-type="react" imagex-version="0.3.10" srcset="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/ecdc11149f4a4ecb89a6556b4674859f_1726505694?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=IXb03DcV3sEg0X%2B5Sxt2FX6%2B4C8%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 1x, https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/ecdc11149f4a4ecb89a6556b4674859f_1726505694?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=IXb03DcV3sEg0X%2B5Sxt2FX6%2B4C8%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 2x" style="position: absolute; inset: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0px; border: none; margin: auto; display: block; width: 0px; height: 0px; min-width: 100%; max-width: 100%; min-height: 100%; max-height: 100%;">
https://www.tiktok.com/@tiffintech/video/7414217699624045829
<img alt="Tiff in Tech 使用 Palali Music 的 sonido original 创作的 What is the difference between SQL and NoSQL?  Think of SQL and NoSQL databases like different types of storage systems. SQL is like a traditional library with strict organization - books are in specific places and there's a detailed catalog. It's great for finding exact information but less flexible. NoSQL is more like a modern, adaptable storage system - think adjustable shelves or bins. It's easier to add new types of items quickly, but might be less organized. SQL works well for applications needing precise data handling, like banking. NoSQL is better for apps dealing with varied, rapidly changing data, like social media. Essentially, SQL is a structured filing system, while NoSQL offers more flexible storage options. #tech #techexplained #developer #coding " fetchpriority="auto" decoding="async" src="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/f2401124223747a5b5b8ec548c55cf7b_1726257091?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=e8tS7w6Ly6I%2BY%2FDfCXhARU3QSOk%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=-" imagex-type="react" imagex-version="0.3.10" srcset="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/f2401124223747a5b5b8ec548c55cf7b_1726257091?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=e8tS7w6Ly6I%2BY%2FDfCXhARU3QSOk%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 1x, https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/f2401124223747a5b5b8ec548c55cf7b_1726257091?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=e8tS7w6Ly6I%2BY%2FDfCXhARU3QSOk%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 2x" style="position: absolute; inset: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0px; border: none; margin: auto; display: block; width: 0px; height: 0px; min-width: 100%; max-width: 100%; min-height: 100%; max-height: 100%;">

<img alt="Tiff in Tech 使用 Palali Music 的 sonido original 创作的 How does Starlink work?  Starlink is a satellite internet constellation operated by SpaceX. It consists of thousands of small satellites in low Earth orbit (LEO), typically at altitudes of 540-570 km. These satellites communicate with ground-based transceivers using phased array antennas and high-frequency Ku and Ka band radio waves. The satellites form a mesh network in space, using laser inter-satellite links to route data between them. This allows for global coverage and reduces latency compared to traditional geostationary satellite internet. Ground stations, called gateways, connect the satellite network to the broader internet infrastructure. User terminals, known as &quot;Starlink dishes,&quot; use electronically steered beams to track and communicate with multiple satellites as they pass overhead, ensuring continuous connectivity. #tech #technology #techexplained " fetchpriority="auto" decoding="async" src="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/o0EIdFNcfEA8CfDhIf52ASAgEd9Q4ur4rDTAjP?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=IBxsX8dhZ%2BK8tT0h5o8Ap1keF7E%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=-" imagex-type="react" imagex-version="0.3.10" srcset="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/o0EIdFNcfEA8CfDhIf52ASAgEd9Q4ur4rDTAjP?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=IBxsX8dhZ%2BK8tT0h5o8Ap1keF7E%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 1x, https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/o0EIdFNcfEA8CfDhIf52ASAgEd9Q4ur4rDTAjP?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=IBxsX8dhZ%2BK8tT0h5o8Ap1keF7E%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 2x" style="position: absolute; inset: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0px; border: none; margin: auto; display: block; width: 0px; height: 0px; min-width: 100%; max-width: 100%; min-height: 100%; max-height: 100%;">

<img alt="Tiff in Tech 使用 Palali Music 的 sonido original 创作的 What is Git?  Git is a distributed version control system that helps developers track and manage changes in their code. A typical Git workflow involves cloning a repository, creating a new branch for a feature or fix, making changes locally, staging these changes with 'git add', committing them with 'git commit', and then pushing the changes to a remote repository with 'git push'. Developers often create a pull request for code review, after which the changes are merged into the main branch. This process allows for collaborative development, easy tracking of project history, and the ability to work on multiple features simultaneously without affecting the main codebase until changes are ready and reviewed. #tech #technology #coding #stem #techtok " fetchpriority="auto" decoding="async" src="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/69cd2255def1456a9427fa5cfc12d432_1725296221?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=QWIgiiqTGouhsL3ry7jdexuxbAM%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=-" imagex-type="react" imagex-version="0.3.10" srcset="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/69cd2255def1456a9427fa5cfc12d432_1725296221?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=QWIgiiqTGouhsL3ry7jdexuxbAM%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 1x, https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/69cd2255def1456a9427fa5cfc12d432_1725296221?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=QWIgiiqTGouhsL3ry7jdexuxbAM%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 2x" style="position: absolute; inset: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0px; border: none; margin: auto; display: block; width: 0px; height: 0px; min-width: 100%; max-width: 100%; min-height: 100%; max-height: 100%;">

<img alt="Tiff in Tech 使用 Tiff in Tech 的 original sound 创作的 Netflix uses Chaos Engineering, specifically through their tool known as Chaos Monkey, to enhance the resilience and reliability of their systems, ensuring a seamless streaming experience for users worldwide. Chaos Engineering involves injecting controlled chaos into systems to identify and address potential weaknesses. Chaos Monkey plays a central role in this process by randomly terminating instances in Netflix's production environment. This simulation of real-world failures allows engineers to observe how systems respond and to improve fault tolerance. By embracing the unpredictability of failures, Netflix engineers are able to strengthen their architecture, ensuring that it can handle disruptions gracefully and maintain uninterrupted service for users. This approach to system design not only improves reliability but also prepares the infrastructure to withstand and quickly recover from unforeseen challenges. #tech #technology #techexplained " fetchpriority="auto" decoding="async" src="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/owlKaVIIECgNd7peXKLSS7TfrzYcBIAeGCFjAP?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=W6N%2FjoAVSE7KFN6HQiSWv%2FBPaLY%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=-" imagex-type="react" imagex-version="0.3.10" srcset="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/owlKaVIIECgNd7peXKLSS7TfrzYcBIAeGCFjAP?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=W6N%2FjoAVSE7KFN6HQiSWv%2FBPaLY%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 1x, https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/owlKaVIIECgNd7peXKLSS7TfrzYcBIAeGCFjAP?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=W6N%2FjoAVSE7KFN6HQiSWv%2FBPaLY%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 2x" style="position: absolute; inset: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0px; border: none; margin: auto; display: block; width: 0px; height: 0px; min-width: 100%; max-width: 100%; min-height: 100%; max-height: 100%;">

<img alt="Tiff in Tech 使用 Tiff in Tech 的 original sound 创作的 Why dont hackers just shut down the entire internet?! There are two critical systems that, if compromised, could cause massive disruptions: BGP and DNS. BGP, is like the internet's traffic control system. It decides how data is routed across the globe. In 2022, a BGP mishap actually rerouted a large chunk of European mobile internet traffic to China! While not a deliberate attack, it shows how BGP vulnerabilities can cause widespread issues. Then there's DNS. Think of it as the internet's phonebook. In 2016, an attack on Dyn's DNS servers took down major websites across the US for hours. But here's where it gets interesting. While hackers might struggle to &quot;shut down&quot; the internet globally, governments have managed to do it on a national scale. During the Arab Spring, Egypt effectively turned off internet access for its citizens. China's Great Firewall is another example, filtering web content nationwide. These government-level shutdowns often work by interfering with critical services or controlling the physical infrastructure connecting to the global network. They can make the internet appear broken, even if the underlying connection still exists. A global internet shutdown by hackers is unlikely thanks to the network's decentralized nature, localized or national disruptions are a real concern.  #tech #technology #stem #techexplained #techtok " fetchpriority="auto" decoding="async" src="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/928fb939451042158fe1ba1b8470804c_1724888327?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=vuK3v6jdpwB13fnrIAofZ6BTZj0%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=-" imagex-type="react" imagex-version="0.3.10" srcset="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/928fb939451042158fe1ba1b8470804c_1724888327?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=vuK3v6jdpwB13fnrIAofZ6BTZj0%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 1x, https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/928fb939451042158fe1ba1b8470804c_1724888327?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=vuK3v6jdpwB13fnrIAofZ6BTZj0%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 2x" style="position: absolute; inset: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0px; border: none; margin: auto; display: block; width: 0px; height: 0px; min-width: 100%; max-width: 100%; min-height: 100%; max-height: 100%;">

<img alt="Tiff in Tech 使用 Tiff in Tech 的 original sound 创作的 How does cloud storage keep expanding?! I haven’t deleted anything since 2010!  When you upload a file to cloud storage, your device first chunks the file into smaller pieces. These chunks are then sent over the internet using HTTPS to the cloud provider's servers. Upon receipt, the data center's load balancer directs the incoming chunks to available storage servers. The file is reassembled, and its metadata (like filename, size, and owner) is recorded in a distributed database. The file is then encrypted using a method like AES-256 and stored across multiple physical devices for redundancy. A unique identifier for the file is generated and sent back to your device. Simultaneously, the storage system updates its distributed file table, making the file quickly accessible from any connected device. If the file already exists, deduplication algorithms may prevent storing duplicate data, instead just updating metadata to link your account to the existing file. This entire process, from upload initiation to confirmation, typically occurs within seconds, leveraging high-speed networks and optimized data handling protocols. #tech #technology #coding #stem #techtok " fetchpriority="auto" decoding="async" src="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/1686cb228e6746de894a9d240249c0a1_1724880845?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=oQcuVMPbXsjYn0lMiRQdxOCdtb8%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=-" imagex-type="react" imagex-version="0.3.10" srcset="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/1686cb228e6746de894a9d240249c0a1_1724880845?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=oQcuVMPbXsjYn0lMiRQdxOCdtb8%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 1x, https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/1686cb228e6746de894a9d240249c0a1_1724880845?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=oQcuVMPbXsjYn0lMiRQdxOCdtb8%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 2x" style="position: absolute; inset: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0px; border: none; margin: auto; display: block; width: 0px; height: 0px; min-width: 100%; max-width: 100%; min-height: 100%; max-height: 100%;">

<img alt="Tiff in Tech 使用 Tiff in Tech 的 original sound 创作的 Is Telegram really the most secure messaging app?!  When a user sends a message on Telegram, the app immediately encrypts it on their device using the MTProto protocol. For secret chats, this encryption is end-to-end, meaning only the intended recipient can decrypt it. The encrypted message then travels through Telegram's distributed network of servers, which are spread across various countries to enhance security. As the message moves, it benefits from perfect forward secrecy, ensuring that even if future encryption keys are compromised, past messages remain secure. The message arrives at the recipient's device, where it's decrypted and displayed. If it's a self-destructing message, it will vanish after the set time. Throughout this process, Telegram's open-source client code allows for independent security verification, while features like two-step verification and the absence of cloud backups add extra layers of protection.  #tech #technology #stem #coding " fetchpriority="auto" decoding="async" src="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/0f596c20ddda4d4aaf1b75e570b88aa2_1724447510?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=MyRu%2Fsnuu%2B1s5V3TIJEJ70eutu4%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=-" imagex-type="react" imagex-version="0.3.10" srcset="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/0f596c20ddda4d4aaf1b75e570b88aa2_1724447510?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=MyRu%2Fsnuu%2B1s5V3TIJEJ70eutu4%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 1x, https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/0f596c20ddda4d4aaf1b75e570b88aa2_1724447510?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=MyRu%2Fsnuu%2B1s5V3TIJEJ70eutu4%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 2x" style="position: absolute; inset: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0px; border: none; margin: auto; display: block; width: 0px; height: 0px; min-width: 100%; max-width: 100%; min-height: 100%; max-height: 100%;">

<img alt="Tiff in Tech 使用 Gold-Tiger 的 Funny 创作的 ✨its an investment ✨ #tech #technology #coding #stem " fetchpriority="auto" decoding="async" src="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/osvvSLGujICuegs33dIQ2VCAeKxgPQFTjNeM5s?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=6M932ZKErELyV762js9K3%2BEC7LU%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=-" imagex-type="react" imagex-version="0.3.10" srcset="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/osvvSLGujICuegs33dIQ2VCAeKxgPQFTjNeM5s?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=6M932ZKErELyV762js9K3%2BEC7LU%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 1x, https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/osvvSLGujICuegs33dIQ2VCAeKxgPQFTjNeM5s?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=6M932ZKErELyV762js9K3%2BEC7LU%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 2x" style="position: absolute; inset: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0px; border: none; margin: auto; display: block; width: 0px; height: 0px; min-width: 100%; max-width: 100%; min-height: 100%; max-height: 100%;">

<img alt="Tiff in Tech 使用 Tiff in Tech 的 original sound 创作的 How come Face ID never mistakes you?  Have you ever wondered how is face ID able to recognize you whether you have glasses, a beard, or completely change up your look? But yet it never mistakes you for someone else, you can never unlock someone else's phone. Now, face I.D. doesn't just store one single image of your face, but rather continually updates and learns every single time you unlock your phone. And this allows it to adapt to gradual changes over time. The system is designed to recognize depth and contours rather than surface level details, so it's less affected by things such as facial hair or glasses. It also focuses on stable features of your face, things such as the distance between your eyes, the height of your cheekbones, things that don't change that much. Even when you put on glasses or have a beard. Moreover, face ID uses something called partial matching and can store multiple appearances for a single user. So even if you do grow a beard, color your hair or change up your appearance, it might create an alternate appearance while still retaining data from the original. And it's this combination of 3D technology, machine learning and adaptive design that allows face ID to be extremely accurate. So accurate to the point that even twins can't unlock each other's phones. <img alt="Tiff in Tech 使用 Tiff in Tech 的 original sound 创作的 Why isnt there alwaya free wifi on planes?!  The lack of free Wi-Fi on airplanes in 2024 is due to both financial incentives for airlines and technical limitations. To offer Wi-Fi, planes require antennas, a network modem, and wireless access points, with retrofitting existing aircraft being expensive and time-consuming. Wi-Fi connectivity is achieved either through satellite antennas or air-to-ground (ATG) antennas. ATG antennas face challenges over large bodies of water, leading to reliance on satellite Wi-Fi, which uses orbiting satellites for data transmission, ensuring continuous connectivity. Airlines often use a hybrid of both systems. While charging for Wi-Fi does generate extra revenue for airlines, it also manages bandwidth limitations. With potentially hundreds of passengers wanting to use the service, making it free would overwhelm the limited bandwidth, degrading the quality for everyone. Hence, airlines charge for Wi-Fi to limit the number of users and maintain service quality. #tech #stem #technology #techexplained #techexpert " fetchpriority="auto" decoding="async" src="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/oQeifwVAFCEIl8AspxGfkaQCfIyXZ7GQ9LMRlN?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=fioBoLFz6yOUVnSDZjnvoJhtW94%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=-" imagex-type="react" imagex-version="0.3.10" srcset="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/oQeifwVAFCEIl8AspxGfkaQCfIyXZ7GQ9LMRlN?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=fioBoLFz6yOUVnSDZjnvoJhtW94%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 1x, https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/oQeifwVAFCEIl8AspxGfkaQCfIyXZ7GQ9LMRlN?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=fioBoLFz6yOUVnSDZjnvoJhtW94%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 2x" style="position: absolute; inset: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0px; border: none; margin: auto; display: block; width: 0px; height: 0px; min-width: 100%; max-width: 100%; min-height: 100%; max-height: 100%;">

<img alt="Tiff in Tech 使用 Tiff in Tech 的 original sound 创作的 Why does Google Maps never get you lost?  OK maybe it does sometimes but this is pretty cool bow the tech works.  Google Maps never gets you lost thanks to a complex system of technologies. It starts with a massive geospatial database, but static maps aren't enough.  Therefore, it collects real-time data from millions of devices, feeding machine learning models for traffic prediction. But accurate navigation needs more than just predictions. Therefore, Google employs the A* search algorithm, an efficient pathfinding method that finds the optimal route by evaluating both the distance traveled and the estimated distance to the goal.  This algorithm works on a graph of the road network, with edges weighted by current and predicted travel times. But even the best route is useless without knowing where you are.  Therefore, Google fuses data from GPS, Wi-Fi, cellular networks, and device sensors for precise localization. Finally, map-matching algorithms ensure you always appear on the correct road. All this happens in milliseconds, leveraging Google's global network of data centers, to keep you on track no matter where you're headed. #tech #technology #developer #stem #techexpert #techexplained " fetchpriority="auto" decoding="async" src="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/eb6c5e948a20455b86f39f9aaf5eee9d_1723322851?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=mlkUPDlMZHIByV8%2FLSjrkJud9rc%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=-" imagex-type="react" imagex-version="0.3.10" srcset="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/eb6c5e948a20455b86f39f9aaf5eee9d_1723322851?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=mlkUPDlMZHIByV8%2FLSjrkJud9rc%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 1x, https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/eb6c5e948a20455b86f39f9aaf5eee9d_1723322851?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=mlkUPDlMZHIByV8%2FLSjrkJud9rc%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 2x" style="position: absolute; inset: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0px; border: none; margin: auto; display: block; width: 0px; height: 0px; min-width: 100%; max-width: 100%; min-height: 100%; max-height: 100%;">

<img alt="Tiff in Tech 使用 Tiff in Tech 的 original sound 创作的 What was the first high-level programming language? While there were many programming languages that came before this... here is the first high-level one!  Fortran (Formula Translation) is widely recognized as the first high-level programming language to achieve widespread use. Developed by a team at IBM led by John Backus, Fortran was first released in 1957. It marked a significant leap forward in programming technology, allowing scientists and engineers to write complex mathematical formulas in a way that was much closer to standard mathematical notation than previous assembly languages. This made it considerably easier for non-specialists to write programs, greatly expanding the pool of potential programmers.  #tech #technology #coding #stem " fetchpriority="auto" decoding="async" src="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/oUZzBGdVElEEUrhEu0PQ1QgOniAAniBBy9SIr?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=6wmJ%2FWQgMfySf%2B%2F31x%2FOZIu0z94%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=-" imagex-type="react" imagex-version="0.3.10" srcset="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/oUZzBGdVElEEUrhEu0PQ1QgOniAAniBBy9SIr?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=6wmJ%2FWQgMfySf%2B%2F31x%2FOZIu0z94%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 1x, https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/oUZzBGdVElEEUrhEu0PQ1QgOniAAniBBy9SIr?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=6wmJ%2FWQgMfySf%2B%2F31x%2FOZIu0z94%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 2x" style="position: absolute; inset: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0px; border: none; margin: auto; display: block; width: 0px; height: 0px; min-width: 100%; max-width: 100%; min-height: 100%; max-height: 100%;">

<img alt="Tiff in Tech 使用 Palali Music 的 sonido original 创作的 What is the difference between OAuth and JWT?  OAuth and JWT are both used in authentication processes, but they serve different purposes. OAuth is an authorization framework that allows third-party applications to access user resources without sharing credentials, often used when one service needs to access data from another on behalf of a user. JWT, or JSON Web Token, is like a secure digital ID card for computers. It's a compact way to securely transmit information about a user between parties as a JSON object. When you log in, instead of checking your credentials every time, the server gives you a JWT containing information about your identity and permissions. This token has three parts: a header, a payload with claims about you, and a signature to ensure it hasn't been tampered with. You send this token with each request, allowing the server to quickly verify who you are without constant database lookups. In a real-world scenario, a photo printing service might use OAuth to access a user's Google Photos for printing, while using JWT to manage the user's session within its own application. The choice between them depends on the specific authentication and authorization needs of the application. #tech #technology #developer #stem #education " fetchpriority="auto" decoding="async" src="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/oMmGJDyvhBeEqAFRzB6I2r4BQsE2QPfGDmqDEj?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=qbc0FixPlURa77XeVClkEWWOBOQ%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=-" imagex-type="react" imagex-version="0.3.10" srcset="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/oMmGJDyvhBeEqAFRzB6I2r4BQsE2QPfGDmqDEj?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=qbc0FixPlURa77XeVClkEWWOBOQ%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 1x, https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/oMmGJDyvhBeEqAFRzB6I2r4BQsE2QPfGDmqDEj?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=qbc0FixPlURa77XeVClkEWWOBOQ%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 2x" style="position: absolute; inset: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0px; border: none; margin: auto; display: block; width: 0px; height: 0px; min-width: 100%; max-width: 100%; min-height: 100%; max-height: 100%;">

<img alt="Tiff in Tech 使用 James Jones 的 original sound 创作的 I had no idea Google was originally named that 🤣 1. Email was created before the World Wide Web (WWW): Email was invented in 1971 by Ray Tomlinson, nearly two decades before the World Wide Web. It was designed as a way to send messages between computers on ARPANET, the precursor to the modern internet. The WWW, on the other hand, was created by Tim Berners-Lee in 1989 and became publicly available in 1991.  2. The original name for the search engine Google was BackRub:  In 1996, when Larry Page and Sergey Brin began developing their search engine at Stanford University, they called it &quot;BackRub.&quot; This name was chosen because the system checked backlinks to estimate the importance of a site. The project was renamed &quot;Google&quot; in 1997, a play on the mathematical term &quot;googol&quot; (1 followed by 100 zeros). 3. The first text message ever sent was &quot;Merry Christmas&quot; in 1992: On December 3, 1992, Neil Papworth, a 22-year-old software programmer, sent the first SMS text message from a computer to a mobile phone. The recipient was Richard Jarvis, a director at Vodafon #tech #technology #developer #stem #techexplained " fetchpriority="auto" decoding="async" src="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/c6607996f9f74001861bdf81101394c1_1722799918?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=LQ%2BtmygyFmupxWeNnYP75VL%2BQl8%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=-" imagex-type="react" imagex-version="0.3.10" srcset="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/c6607996f9f74001861bdf81101394c1_1722799918?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=LQ%2BtmygyFmupxWeNnYP75VL%2BQl8%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 1x, https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/c6607996f9f74001861bdf81101394c1_1722799918?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=LQ%2BtmygyFmupxWeNnYP75VL%2BQl8%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 2x" style="position: absolute; inset: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0px; border: none; margin: auto; display: block; width: 0px; height: 0px; min-width: 100%; max-width: 100%; min-height: 100%; max-height: 100%;">

<img alt="Tiff in Tech 使用 Tiff in Tech 的 original sound 创作的 Why does X never crash during major world events when everyone is tweeting?  Okay there have been a few times it has crashed but here is why it typically can handle so many tweets.  X's ability to handle major world events stems from its sophisticated infrastructure and traffic management. The platform uses a distributed architecture spread across global data centers, allowing for flexible scaling. Advanced load balancing distributes incoming requests efficiently, while extensive caching and Content Delivery Networks speed up content delivery. X implements data sharding to optimize database operations and utilizes cloud-based auto-scaling to adjust resources dynamically. These techniques, combined with robust monitoring and failover systems, enable X to maintain stability during high-traffic periods. However, like any complex system, X isn't immune to occasional disruptions during extreme events and may employ temporary feature limitations to preserve core functionality when necessary.  #tech #stem #techexpert #techexplained " fetchpriority="auto" decoding="async" src="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/oAaNWBGfECCIbuXReIAgIi9L2tt7pfYJidmjSa?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=UO45ZoeyDIW6sdGMqEbz2PMvMAg%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=-" imagex-type="react" imagex-version="0.3.10" srcset="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/oAaNWBGfECCIbuXReIAgIi9L2tt7pfYJidmjSa?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=UO45ZoeyDIW6sdGMqEbz2PMvMAg%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 1x, https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/oAaNWBGfECCIbuXReIAgIi9L2tt7pfYJidmjSa?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=UO45ZoeyDIW6sdGMqEbz2PMvMAg%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 2x" style="position: absolute; inset: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0px; border: none; margin: auto; display: block; width: 0px; height: 0px; min-width: 100%; max-width: 100%; min-height: 100%; max-height: 100%;">

<img alt="Tiff in Tech 使用 Cupidon &amp; Milaa 的 Feel It 创作的 Did you know you were helping train AI this way?  Are you training A.I. when using these? Also, I don't know about you, but I overthink these terribly. Okay, but here's how they work technically. But first, did you know the founder of Duolingo is also the founder of the tech behind these CAPTCHAs? Pretty crazy. User solves CAPTCHA. They're typically presented with two images or two words. One is known in the system or the control, and the other is unknown and needs labeling. That's where the help of you comes in by correctly solving the challenge. Your response to the unknown item is considered reliable, but it brings up a question If the other item is not known to the system, how does it know if you actually got it right? One way is through consensus verification. The same unknown item is shown to multiple users going through selecting the right image or text. And then based on that, a consensus is formed on the most common answers. It's pretty cool. <img alt="Tiff in Tech 使用 iMi🫧 的 Dominic x Brazil Declan 创作的 Dont miss out on these three prompts for job hunting 👇 1️⃣Resume review and alignment prompt: &quot;Please review my resume and the following job posting, then provide a detailed analysis: [Paste your resume here] [Paste the job posting here] Analyze the alignment between my resume and the job requirements. Identify any gaps or mismatches. Suggest specific modifications to my resume, including: Skills or experiences I should emphasize Achievements that align with the job requirements Keywords from the job posting that I should incorporate Sections that need expansion or reduction Any irrelevant information that should be removed Provide a bullet-point list of recommended changes, followed by a brief explanation for each suggestion. Finally, offer 2-3 overall tips to make my resume more compelling for this specific position.&quot; 2️⃣Customized cover letter creation prompt: &quot;Please help me create a customized cover letter for the following job posting: [Paste the job posting here] Here's a brief summary of my relevant experience and skills: [Provide a 3-5 sentence overview of your background] Please write a cover letter that: Addresses the hiring manager (use 'Dear Hiring Manager' if no name is provided) Opens with a strong, attention-grabbing first paragraph Highlights 3-4 of my most relevant skills or experiences that match the job requirements Includes a specific example of a relevant achievement Demonstrates my knowledge of the company and why I'm interested in the position Closes with a call to action and my enthusiasm for the role The tone should be professional yet personable. Keep the letter to about 300-400 words. After the letter, please provide a brief explanation of why you chose to emphasize certain points.&quot; 3️⃣Personalized LinkedIn outreach message prompt: &quot;Please help me craft a personalized LinkedIn message to reach out to [Company Name] about potential job opportunities. Here's some relevant information: My name: [Your Name] My current role: [Your Current Job Title] My target role at the company: [Desired Position] Company's recent news or achievement: [Brief description of recent company news] My relevant skills or experiences: [List 2-3 key points] Mutual connection (if any): [Name and role of mutual connection] Create a message that: Starts with a personalized greeting Briefly introduces myself and my interest in the company Mentions the company's recent news or achievement Highlights how my skills align with their needs Includes a soft request for information about opportunities or to connect Keeps the tone professional, enthusiastic, and concise (about 100-150 words) After the message, please provide 2-3 tips on LinkedIn outreach etiquette and best practices. #tech #career #stem " fetchpriority="auto" decoding="async" src="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/38c3cb996ff241ce9e936f568b47ecdf_1721690456?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=495qFahnlB6lV9VI4ZqWYul2zpI%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=-" imagex-type="react" imagex-version="0.3.10" srcset="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/38c3cb996ff241ce9e936f568b47ecdf_1721690456?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=495qFahnlB6lV9VI4ZqWYul2zpI%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 1x, https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/38c3cb996ff241ce9e936f568b47ecdf_1721690456?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=495qFahnlB6lV9VI4ZqWYul2zpI%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 2x" style="position: absolute; inset: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0px; border: none; margin: auto; display: block; width: 0px; height: 0px; min-width: 100%; max-width: 100%; min-height: 100%; max-height: 100%;">

<img alt="Tiff in Tech 使用 Tommy Richman 的 DEVIL IS A LIE 创作的 The last one has happened to so many people. Important to be aware!  Deleting a file doesn't actually erase it from your computer  (TRUE): When you &quot;delete&quot; a file normally, the operating system only removes the file's entry from the file system table. The actual data remains on the storage device until it's overwritten by new data. Strong passwords alone are enough to protect accounts (FALSE):  While strong passwords are important, they're not sufficient on their own. Multi-factor authentication and regular password changes add crucial extra layers of security. Emails from known contacts are always safe (FALSE): Hackers can compromise email accounts or spoof familiar addresses. Always verify unexpected requests or links, even from known contacts, to guard against phishing attempts. #tech #technology #stem " fetchpriority="auto" decoding="async" src="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/f60178a116ce418487d01802dc1e2fca_1720636904?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=yy9l5%2BBCxGTdegOUBxiAfICjMCE%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=-" imagex-type="react" imagex-version="0.3.10" srcset="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/f60178a116ce418487d01802dc1e2fca_1720636904?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=yy9l5%2BBCxGTdegOUBxiAfICjMCE%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 1x, https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/f60178a116ce418487d01802dc1e2fca_1720636904?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=yy9l5%2BBCxGTdegOUBxiAfICjMCE%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 2x" style="position: absolute; inset: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0px; border: none; margin: auto; display: block; width: 0px; height: 0px; min-width: 100%; max-width: 100%; min-height: 100%; max-height: 100%;">

<img alt="Tiff in Tech 使用 Tiff in Tech 的 original sound 创作的 Is this the next big thing in tech after AI?  Quantum computing is like a super-powered calculator that can solve complex problems much faster than current computers. It could revolutionize fields like medicine, finance, and AI, potentially leading to quicker disease cures, better market predictions, and smarter AI. However, it poses a significant challenge to current encryption methods, potentially compromising data security. On the flip side, it could also create new, unbreakable encryption techniques. The question remains: Is quantum computing the next big tech revolution, and are we prepared for its impact? #tech #quantumcomputing #technology #stem #techxplained " fetchpriority="auto" decoding="async" src="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/dc22baf6be564fbcaf49750a1e789ee8_1720381772?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=RvjTAg6YSSfVeyIm3wGgGMC45YY%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=-" imagex-type="react" imagex-version="0.3.10" srcset="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/dc22baf6be564fbcaf49750a1e789ee8_1720381772?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=RvjTAg6YSSfVeyIm3wGgGMC45YY%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 1x, https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/dc22baf6be564fbcaf49750a1e789ee8_1720381772?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=RvjTAg6YSSfVeyIm3wGgGMC45YY%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 2x" style="position: absolute; inset: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0px; border: none; margin: auto; display: block; width: 0px; height: 0px; min-width: 100%; max-width: 100%; min-height: 100%; max-height: 100%;">

Use basic SVG shapes with different colors to represent the player (e.g., blue circle), opponents (e.g., red circles), and collectable items (e.g., gold squares). Include simple sound effects for movements, item collection, and game over. Gradually increase difficulty by speeding up AI movements and adding more opponents as the score increases. Implement this game logic in a single React component, focusing on creating an engaging gameplay loop with clear objectives and escalating challenges. <img alt="Tiff in Tech 使用 Tiff in Tech 的 original sound 创作的 What is the difference between TCP and UDP?  Imagine you're sending a package to a friend. TCP is like using a delivery service that requires a signature and confirmation when the package arrives. It's slower but ensures your package gets there safely and in the correct order. UDP, on the other hand, is like tossing your package over the fence and hoping it lands where it should. It's faster because there's no waiting for confirmation, but some packages might get lost or arrive out of order. In computer networks, TCP is used when accuracy is crucial (like for emails or file transfers), while UDP is used when speed is more important and a few errors are acceptable (like for streaming video or online gaming). #tech #stem #techexplained " fetchpriority="auto" decoding="async" src="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/0b9263744803418e8f9420f9c174d627_1719274892?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=8yh1HVQB83FV7p%2BmtxkeuqRGEyA%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=-" imagex-type="react" imagex-version="0.3.10" srcset="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/0b9263744803418e8f9420f9c174d627_1719274892?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=8yh1HVQB83FV7p%2BmtxkeuqRGEyA%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 1x, https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/0b9263744803418e8f9420f9c174d627_1719274892?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=8yh1HVQB83FV7p%2BmtxkeuqRGEyA%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 2x" style="position: absolute; inset: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0px; border: none; margin: auto; display: block; width: 0px; height: 0px; min-width: 100%; max-width: 100%; min-height: 100%; max-height: 100%;">

<img alt="Tiff in Tech 使用 Tiff in Tech 的 original sound 创作的 What was the first video game created?  Video games have a complex origin story that challenges the notion of a single &quot;first&quot; video game. While many people believe Pong (1972) was the first, earlier inventions laid crucial groundwork. The 1948 Cathode-Ray Tube Amusement Device, 1951's Nimrod computer, and 1952's OXO all contributed to video game development. However, William Higinbotham's &quot;Tennis for Two&quot; (1958) is often cited as the first true video game, as it was designed purely for entertainment and featured moving graphics on screen. Despite these earlier inventions, Pong became the first game to capture wide public attention, popularizing video games for a mass audience. The evolution of video games demonstrates how technological advancements and changing definitions have shaped our understanding of this medium over time. #tech #techexpert #education #stem #techexplained " fetchpriority="auto" decoding="async" src="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/4e85ebf1a08d4ce289e0a684c0f8aeef_1719179185?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=xPdklS6z9OgEQoQxeO%2FEYcstjrM%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=-" imagex-type="react" imagex-version="0.3.10" srcset="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/4e85ebf1a08d4ce289e0a684c0f8aeef_1719179185?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=xPdklS6z9OgEQoQxeO%2FEYcstjrM%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 1x, https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/4e85ebf1a08d4ce289e0a684c0f8aeef_1719179185?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=xPdklS6z9OgEQoQxeO%2FEYcstjrM%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 2x" style="position: absolute; inset: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0px; border: none; margin: auto; display: block; width: 0px; height: 0px; min-width: 100%; max-width: 100%; min-height: 100%; max-height: 100%;">

I created a Python script that uses OpenCV, a computer vision library, to detect when I take a drink of coffee from my mug. The script captures video from my camera, analyzes each frame to detect my face, and focuses on the mouth region. <img alt="Tiff in Tech 使用 Tiff in Tech 的 original sound 创作的 What is the difference between machine learning and deep learning?  Machine learning and deep learning are both subsets of artificial intelligence, but they differ in their approach and complexity. Machine learning involves training algorithms to learn patterns and make predictions from data, without being explicitly programmed. It can be used for tasks like spam detection or recommending products. Deep learning, on the other hand, is a more advanced form of machine learning that uses neural networks with many layers to learn from vast amounts of data. This allows it to tackle more complex problems, such as image and speech recognition, by learning hierarchical representations of data. In essence, deep learning is a more powerful and autonomous version of machine learning, capable of handling more intricate tasks. #tech #machinelearning #coding #technology " fetchpriority="auto" decoding="async" src="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/tos-maliva-p-0068/050f644cb43847338fe631f9e45a2d9d_1718031142~tplv-dmt-logom:tos-useast2a-v-0068/ocAC4ZMuAJjfIFXILiADNIQGOgfSzApEgReTkU.image?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=XuSh1GeVndVlqo0rGYk7RVxC7tQ%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=-" imagex-type="react" imagex-version="0.3.10" srcset="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/tos-maliva-p-0068/050f644cb43847338fe631f9e45a2d9d_1718031142~tplv-dmt-logom:tos-useast2a-v-0068/ocAC4ZMuAJjfIFXILiADNIQGOgfSzApEgReTkU.image?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=XuSh1GeVndVlqo0rGYk7RVxC7tQ%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 1x, https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/tos-maliva-p-0068/050f644cb43847338fe631f9e45a2d9d_1718031142~tplv-dmt-logom:tos-useast2a-v-0068/ocAC4ZMuAJjfIFXILiADNIQGOgfSzApEgReTkU.image?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=XuSh1GeVndVlqo0rGYk7RVxC7tQ%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 2x" style="position: absolute; inset: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0px; border: none; margin: auto; display: block; width: 0px; height: 0px; min-width: 100%; max-width: 100%; min-height: 100%; max-height: 100%;">

<img alt="Tiff in Tech 使用 Tiff in Tech 的 original sound 创作的 What is Kubernetes?  Kubernetes is a tool that helps manage and organize applications running on multiple computers or servers. Think of it as a conductor in an orchestra, making sure all the musicians (applications) are playing together smoothly and efficiently. It allows you to easily deploy, scale, and manage your applications across a cluster of machines. This means you can run your applications reliably, handle more traffic, and update them without downtime. In simple terms, Kubernetes makes it easier to run and manage applications in a world where everything is becoming more distributed and complex. #tech #technology #techexplained #stem " fetchpriority="auto" decoding="async" src="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/3d96c6d29cd64ef99f4dab6b63339a70_1717600389?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=YggTw2rTiqPjAWpWhlAXy2YSddk%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=-" imagex-type="react" imagex-version="0.3.10" srcset="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/3d96c6d29cd64ef99f4dab6b63339a70_1717600389?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=YggTw2rTiqPjAWpWhlAXy2YSddk%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 1x, https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/3d96c6d29cd64ef99f4dab6b63339a70_1717600389?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=YggTw2rTiqPjAWpWhlAXy2YSddk%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 2x" style="position: absolute; inset: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0px; border: none; margin: auto; display: block; width: 0px; height: 0px; min-width: 100%; max-width: 100%; min-height: 100%; max-height: 100%;">
