<img alt="Tiff in Tech 使用 Tiff in Tech 的 original sound 创作的 What is TCP? Explained simply so you dont forget it 👇 TCP, which stands for Transmission Control Protocol, is a fundamental protocol used in computer networks to ensure reliable, ordered, and error-checked delivery of data between applications running on hosts communicating over an IP network. In simple terms, TCP is like a trustworthy postal service for the internet. When you send data using TCP, it breaks the data into smaller, numbered packages and sends them to the recipient. TCP ensures that all the packages arrive in the correct order and without any errors. If a package is lost or damaged along the way, TCP detects this and resends the package until it arrives intact. Once all the packages have been received, TCP reassembles them into the original data, making sure that the recipient gets exactly what was sent. This reliable, ordered delivery makes TCP essential for many applications, such as web browsing, email, and file transfers, where the integrity and completeness of the data are crucial. #tech #stem #technology #techexplained " fetchpriority="auto" decoding="async" src="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/tos-maliva-p-0068/2011bda4e08d425ca0bfce4009e6d105_1717488117~tplv-dmt-logom:tos-useast2a-v-0068/ocIA9m7ECCsAWQR23XQACFEBnkDH9XAHNfuxfJ.image?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=d3AM%2B9GOoV1QmurgNRqwBfgOxd0%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=-" imagex-type="react" imagex-version="0.3.10" srcset="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/tos-maliva-p-0068/2011bda4e08d425ca0bfce4009e6d105_1717488117~tplv-dmt-logom:tos-useast2a-v-0068/ocIA9m7ECCsAWQR23XQACFEBnkDH9XAHNfuxfJ.image?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=d3AM%2B9GOoV1QmurgNRqwBfgOxd0%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 1x, https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/tos-maliva-p-0068/2011bda4e08d425ca0bfce4009e6d105_1717488117~tplv-dmt-logom:tos-useast2a-v-0068/ocIA9m7ECCsAWQR23XQACFEBnkDH9XAHNfuxfJ.image?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=d3AM%2B9GOoV1QmurgNRqwBfgOxd0%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 2x" style="position: absolute; inset: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0px; border: none; margin: auto; display: block; width: 0px; height: 0px; min-width: 100%; max-width: 100%; min-height: 100%; max-height: 100%;">

<img alt="Tiff in Tech 使用 Tommy Richman 的 MILLION DOLLAR BABY (VHS) 创作的 Heres what is actually going on 👇 1. Alexa is actually not always recording you: Until your Echo device detects your chosen wake word.  This is made possible by built-in technology called “keyword spotting” that matches spoken audio to the wake word’s acoustic patterns. 2. Deleting files from your recycle bin doesn’t mean they are fully deleted. Deleted files are marked as available space on your drive and allow this data to be overwritten. <img alt="Tiff in Tech 使用 Tiff in Tech 的 original sound 创作的 What is the difference between a load balancer and a reverse proxy?  A load balancer and a reverse proxy serve different primary purposes, although they share some similarities. A load balancer focuses on distributing incoming network traffic across multiple backend servers to optimize resource usage, maximize throughput, and minimize response time. On the other hand, a reverse proxy acts as an intermediary between clients and servers, providing an additional layer of security, performing tasks such as SSL termination, caching, compression, and URL rewriting before forwarding client requests to the appropriate server. #stem #tech #technology #techexplained " fetchpriority="auto" decoding="async" src="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/tos-maliva-p-0068/6719ea6dbab94aac8612307d6b029330_1717107935~tplv-dmt-logom:tos-useast2a-v-0068/oYExwNQQEbDAWJtFPRCMCmfznAxBREAAIlNrfR.image?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=z2syO6CeK2aWdeMVj283%2BUh8X3k%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=-" imagex-type="react" imagex-version="0.3.10" srcset="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/tos-maliva-p-0068/6719ea6dbab94aac8612307d6b029330_1717107935~tplv-dmt-logom:tos-useast2a-v-0068/oYExwNQQEbDAWJtFPRCMCmfznAxBREAAIlNrfR.image?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=z2syO6CeK2aWdeMVj283%2BUh8X3k%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 1x, https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/tos-maliva-p-0068/6719ea6dbab94aac8612307d6b029330_1717107935~tplv-dmt-logom:tos-useast2a-v-0068/oYExwNQQEbDAWJtFPRCMCmfznAxBREAAIlNrfR.image?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=z2syO6CeK2aWdeMVj283%2BUh8X3k%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 2x" style="position: absolute; inset: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0px; border: none; margin: auto; display: block; width: 0px; height: 0px; min-width: 100%; max-width: 100%; min-height: 100%; max-height: 100%;">

<img alt="Tiff in Tech 使用 Tiff in Tech 的 original sound 创作的 What is RAG in AI?  Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG) is a technique that improves the output of large language models (LLMs) by allowing them to access and reference external knowledge sources before generating a response. LLMs are powerful AI models that can generate human-like text for various tasks, but they may sometimes produce irrelevant or outdated information. RAG enhances LLMs by enabling them to retrieve relevant information from a knowledge base, such as an organization's internal documents or a specific domain's authoritative sources. This retrieved information is then used to guide the LLM in generating more accurate, up-to-date, and context-appropriate responses. The importance of RAG lies in its ability to: 1. Improve the relevance and accuracy of LLM-powered chatbots and applications. 2. Provide a cost-effective way to adapt LLMs to specific domains or knowledge bases without retraining the entire model. 3. Address the limitations of static training data and make LLMs more reliable for real-world use cases. #stem #tech #ai #techexplained #techexpert " fetchpriority="auto" decoding="async" src="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/tos-maliva-p-0068/4e987b116f704b5d8dcfcc6c37a24699_1717025811~tplv-dmt-logom:tos-useast2a-v-0068/oIZBEXqRAGI8hAAAevlIeLAvAFkpfIttGvXfLA.image?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=8TWhJAmGGc53HVeaySYMzhBic8A%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=-" imagex-type="react" imagex-version="0.3.10" srcset="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/tos-maliva-p-0068/4e987b116f704b5d8dcfcc6c37a24699_1717025811~tplv-dmt-logom:tos-useast2a-v-0068/oIZBEXqRAGI8hAAAevlIeLAvAFkpfIttGvXfLA.image?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=8TWhJAmGGc53HVeaySYMzhBic8A%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 1x, https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/tos-maliva-p-0068/4e987b116f704b5d8dcfcc6c37a24699_1717025811~tplv-dmt-logom:tos-useast2a-v-0068/oIZBEXqRAGI8hAAAevlIeLAvAFkpfIttGvXfLA.image?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=8TWhJAmGGc53HVeaySYMzhBic8A%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 2x" style="position: absolute; inset: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0px; border: none; margin: auto; display: block; width: 0px; height: 0px; min-width: 100%; max-width: 100%; min-height: 100%; max-height: 100%;">

<img alt="Tiff in Tech 使用 Tiff in Tech 的 original sound 创作的 The main difference between an API (Application Programming Interface) and an SDK (Software Development Kit) lies in their scope and purpose. An API is a set of rules, protocols, and tools that allows different software applications to communicate and exchange data with each other. It defines how developers can request information or functionality from another application, specifying the types of requests and responses. In contrast, an SDK is a more comprehensive package that includes a collection of tools, libraries, documentation, code samples, and guides to help developers build applications for a specific platform or system. SDKs often include APIs as part of their toolkit, but they provide a broader set of resources to facilitate development within a particular ecosystem, enabling developers to get started more quickly and efficiently. #tech #techexplained #developer #stem " fetchpriority="auto" decoding="async" src="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/11be4e90db1b40aa9592c88862aa0530_1716670166?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=Yz1QSD1w%2FxAhn%2BnnxWW1AqlUIGg%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=-" imagex-type="react" imagex-version="0.3.10" srcset="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/11be4e90db1b40aa9592c88862aa0530_1716670166?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=Yz1QSD1w%2FxAhn%2BnnxWW1AqlUIGg%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 1x, https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/11be4e90db1b40aa9592c88862aa0530_1716670166?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=Yz1QSD1w%2FxAhn%2BnnxWW1AqlUIGg%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 2x" style="position: absolute; inset: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0px; border: none; margin: auto; display: block; width: 0px; height: 0px; min-width: 100%; max-width: 100%; min-height: 100%; max-height: 100%;">

<img alt="Tiff in Tech 使用 Tiff in Tech 的 original sound 创作的 What is Kubernetes?!  Here are three key points to remember about Kubernetes: 1. Container orchestration: Kubernetes is a container orchestration platform that manages and coordinates containerized applications across a cluster of machines, ensuring they run efficiently and reliably. 2. Scalability and self-healing: Kubernetes allows you to easily scale applications up or down based on demand and automatically recovers from failures, such as restarting or replacing failed containers or nodes. 3. Infrastructure abstraction: Kubernetes abstracts away the complexities of the underlying infrastructure, allowing developers to focus on building and deploying applications without worrying about the specific details of the hardware or networking. #tech #techexplained #coding #stem #developer " fetchpriority="auto" decoding="async" src="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/eeb6175587704219ac170ddd9ce4034c_1716253642?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=cyOjjUIcUA23XObtogihLo3M1kw%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=-" imagex-type="react" imagex-version="0.3.10" srcset="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/eeb6175587704219ac170ddd9ce4034c_1716253642?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=cyOjjUIcUA23XObtogihLo3M1kw%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 1x, https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/eeb6175587704219ac170ddd9ce4034c_1716253642?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=cyOjjUIcUA23XObtogihLo3M1kw%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 2x" style="position: absolute; inset: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0px; border: none; margin: auto; display: block; width: 0px; height: 0px; min-width: 100%; max-width: 100%; min-height: 100%; max-height: 100%;">

<img alt="Tiff in Tech 使用 Tiff in Tech 的 original sound 创作的 What is Kubernetes? Kubernetes is an open-source container orchestration platform that automates the deployment, scaling, and management of containerized applications. Here's a simple explanation of how it works: 1. Containers: Applications are packaged into containers, which are lightweight and portable units that contain everything needed to run the application (code, libraries, dependencies, etc.). 2. Clusters: Kubernetes organizes containers into clusters, which are groups of machines (nodes) that work together to run applications. 3. Pods: Containers are grouped into pods, which are the smallest deployable units in Kubernetes. Pods can contain one or more containers that share the same resources and network. 4. Deployments: Kubernetes uses deployments to manage the lifecycle of pods, ensuring that the desired number of replicas are running and updating them when necessary. 5. Services: Kubernetes uses services to provide a stable network endpoint for accessing pods, allowing them to communicate with each other and with the outside world. 6. Scaling: Kubernetes can automatically scale the number of pods up or down based on resource usage or other metrics, ensuring that applications can handle variable workloads. In summary, Kubernetes provides a way to efficiently manage and scale containerized applications across a cluster of machines, making it easier to deploy, update, and maintain complex applications in a distributed environment. #tech #stem #techexplained " fetchpriority="auto" decoding="async" src="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/ooZBBvkxgTBSiOhE4GIoMQzAE7CIAPiUxS4tY?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=tx960SB0bFJN3qZ6yoGuKbTrFAo%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=-" imagex-type="react" imagex-version="0.3.10" srcset="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/ooZBBvkxgTBSiOhE4GIoMQzAE7CIAPiUxS4tY?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=tx960SB0bFJN3qZ6yoGuKbTrFAo%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 1x, https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/ooZBBvkxgTBSiOhE4GIoMQzAE7CIAPiUxS4tY?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=tx960SB0bFJN3qZ6yoGuKbTrFAo%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 2x" style="position: absolute; inset: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0px; border: none; margin: auto; display: block; width: 0px; height: 0px; min-width: 100%; max-width: 100%; min-height: 100%; max-height: 100%;">

<img alt="Tiff in Tech 使用 Tiff in Tech 的 original sound 创作的 What is the difference between a forward and reverse proxy?  Reverse Proxy: - Load balancing: Distributes traffic across multiple servers - Increased security: Acts as a single entry point, hiding backend servers - Caching: Improves performance by serving cached content - SSL termination: Handles SSL encryption, reducing load on backend servers - Real-world example: Netflix uses a combination of NGINX and Amazon Web Services (AWS) Elastic Load Balancer (ELB) as a reverse proxy to handle massive traffic and ensure smooth content delivery to its users worldwide. Forward Proxy: - Anonymity: Hides client IP address from the target server - Access control: Allows or blocks access to specific websites or content - Caching: Reduces bandwidth usage and improves performance for frequently accessed content - Content filtering: Blocks inappropriate or malicious content based on predefined rules - Real-world example: Many organizations, such as schools and businesses, use forward proxies like Squid or FortiGate to control and monitor internet access, block inappropriate content, and protect their network from external threats" fetchpriority="auto" decoding="async" src="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/5473c879f7714bac97b59aebc3f56a81_1715791710?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=K5n2FfzV9T1KaGZGtMdSUIVXX2g%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=-" imagex-type="react" imagex-version="0.3.10" srcset="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/5473c879f7714bac97b59aebc3f56a81_1715791710?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=K5n2FfzV9T1KaGZGtMdSUIVXX2g%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 1x, https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/5473c879f7714bac97b59aebc3f56a81_1715791710?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=K5n2FfzV9T1KaGZGtMdSUIVXX2g%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 2x" style="position: absolute; inset: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0px; border: none; margin: auto; display: block; width: 0px; height: 0px; min-width: 100%; max-width: 100%; min-height: 100%; max-height: 100%;">

<img alt="Tiff in Tech 使用 Tiff in Tech 的 original sound 创作的 Why do apps load the beginning of many videos instead of fully loading just one when you don't have internet service? Apps like TikTok and YouTube partially preload multiple videos instead of fully loading one for several reasons: 1. It allows users to quickly switch between videos, providing a smoother browsing experience. 2. It optimizes bandwidth usage, reducing data consumption for both the user and the platform. 3. It accommodates uncertainty about which video the user will watch entirely. 4. It manages device resources more efficiently by distributing memory and processing power across multiple videos. 5. It adapts to variable network conditions, prioritizing which videos to continue buffering. 6. It balances user experience and cost-effectiveness for the platform. #tech #stem #techexpert #techexplained  " fetchpriority="auto" decoding="async" src="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/55058df841a143908e7708574412458f_1715445425?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=5F5topJVEKl%2BklvrUQ%2B4RJAzuGk%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=-" imagex-type="react" imagex-version="0.3.10" srcset="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/55058df841a143908e7708574412458f_1715445425?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=5F5topJVEKl%2BklvrUQ%2B4RJAzuGk%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 1x, https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/55058df841a143908e7708574412458f_1715445425?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=5F5topJVEKl%2BklvrUQ%2B4RJAzuGk%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 2x" style="position: absolute; inset: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0px; border: none; margin: auto; display: block; width: 0px; height: 0px; min-width: 100%; max-width: 100%; min-height: 100%; max-height: 100%;">

<img alt="Tiff in Tech 使用 Tiff in Tech 的 original sound 创作的 Who invented Wifi? Hedy Lamarr was an Austrian-American actress and inventor who pioneered the technology that would one day form the basis for today's WiFi, GPS, and Bluetooth communication systems. While many people and organizations were involved, the person who contributed the most to the WiFi we know today is Vic Hayes. Many consider Hayes, who invented WiFi and call him “the father of WiFi.” Wi-Fi 6, also known as 802.11ax, is the latest generation of Wi-Fi technology, succeeding Wi-Fi 5 (802.11ac).  2.4 GHz is better for longer-range and compatibility but faces more interference and offers slower speeds. 5 GHz provides faster speeds and less interference but has a shorter range and requires more modern devices. 6 GHz (Wi-Fi 6E) offers the highest speeds and least interference but is limited in terms of device compatibility and range. #tech #techexplained #stem #coding " fetchpriority="auto" decoding="async" src="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/ogb89ZKIP2hjiAIiaBB6PQUPZBSO9skiEiw3E?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=L2MlDA7LdN6uqKFcRdTji06%2FQkE%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=-" imagex-type="react" imagex-version="0.3.10" srcset="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/ogb89ZKIP2hjiAIiaBB6PQUPZBSO9skiEiw3E?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=L2MlDA7LdN6uqKFcRdTji06%2FQkE%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 1x, https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/ogb89ZKIP2hjiAIiaBB6PQUPZBSO9skiEiw3E?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=L2MlDA7LdN6uqKFcRdTji06%2FQkE%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 2x" style="position: absolute; inset: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0px; border: none; margin: auto; display: block; width: 0px; height: 0px; min-width: 100%; max-width: 100%; min-height: 100%; max-height: 100%;">

<img alt="Tiff in Tech 使用 Tiff in Tech 的 original sound 创作的 What is a container in tech? But explained simply….  Here are  containers other than Docket (which we here about the most)  1. LXC (Linux Containers): LXC is a container runtime that provides a virtual environment with its own process and network space. It's one of the oldest container technologies and forms the foundation for many other container runtimes. 2. LXD: LXD is a container hypervisor that builds on top of LXC. It provides a more user-friendly interface and additional features like live migration and storage management. 3. containerd: containerd is a standalone container runtime that was originally part of the Docker project. It's a lightweight, portable container runtime that focuses on simplicity and robustness. 4. CRI-O: CRI-O is a container runtime that implements the Kubernetes Container Runtime Interface (CRI). It's designed to be lightweight and optimized for Kubernetes. 5. Podman: Podman is a daemonless container engine that's compatible with the Docker CLI. It allows users to run containers as regular users, without requiring root privileges. 6. Rkt (Rocket): Rkt is a container engine developed by CoreOS (now part of Red Hat). It's designed to be composable, secure, and compatible with the App Container (appc) specification. 7. Windows Containers: Windows Containers is Microsoft's container technology that allows running Windows applications in isolated environments on Windows servers. #tech #technology #coding #stem #education " fetchpriority="auto" decoding="async" src="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/96bd45e499f24d70b25f19001967fcd9_1714857260?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=h5ODfLZSLpNpb25OAis%2BFAfnpos%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=-" imagex-type="react" imagex-version="0.3.10" srcset="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/96bd45e499f24d70b25f19001967fcd9_1714857260?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=h5ODfLZSLpNpb25OAis%2BFAfnpos%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 1x, https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/96bd45e499f24d70b25f19001967fcd9_1714857260?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=h5ODfLZSLpNpb25OAis%2BFAfnpos%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 2x" style="position: absolute; inset: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0px; border: none; margin: auto; display: block; width: 0px; height: 0px; min-width: 100%; max-width: 100%; min-height: 100%; max-height: 100%;">

<img alt="Tiff in Tech 使用 Tiff in Tech 的 original sound 创作的 What is a Websocket and how is it different than HTTPS? A websocket is a communication protocol that allows real-time, bi-directional data transfer between a client and a server over a single, persistent connection. It's like having a telephone conversation, where both parties can send messages to each other at any time, without the need for a request-response cycle like in the traditional HTTP model. WebSocket is efficient, reducing overhead by eliminating HTTP headers, and is ideal for applications requiring real-time updates, such as chat apps, live feeds, or multi-player games. The server can push data to the client as soon as it's available, without the client having to poll for updates. To establish a WebSocket connection, the client sends an HTTP request with an &quot;Upgrade&quot; header, and if the server supports WebSocket, the connection is upgraded. From then on, the client and server can send messages using the WebSocket API, simplifying the development of real-time applications.  #tech #techexpert #techexplained #stem " fetchpriority="auto" decoding="async" src="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/b3ce90f6c250447b917997aec69b94ce_1714602496?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=INj6BBUkWhfU0fTK%2BHlZssEnpjc%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=-" imagex-type="react" imagex-version="0.3.10" srcset="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/b3ce90f6c250447b917997aec69b94ce_1714602496?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=INj6BBUkWhfU0fTK%2BHlZssEnpjc%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 1x, https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/b3ce90f6c250447b917997aec69b94ce_1714602496?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=INj6BBUkWhfU0fTK%2BHlZssEnpjc%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 2x" style="position: absolute; inset: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0px; border: none; margin: auto; display: block; width: 0px; height: 0px; min-width: 100%; max-width: 100%; min-height: 100%; max-height: 100%;">

<img alt="Tiff in Tech 使用 Tiff in Tech 的 original sound 创作的 Why do so many people use DuckDuckGo to stay private? How private is it ...really? DuckDuckGo prioritizes user privacy, therefore it's a popular alternative to data-tracking search giants. Your searches are anonymous because it doesn't track IP addresses, use cookies, or create profiles. DuckDuckGo prevents sites from seeing your search terms, therefore enhancing privacy. But it can't hide your use of the search engine from your ISP. DuckDuckGo's privacy commitment extends to its browser apps and extensions, which block trackers and minimize data collection, therefore providing a comprehensive privacy ecosystem.  But it can't protect you from malicious websites, therefore caution is still necessary.  DuckDuckGo's open-source approach allows independent privacy audits, therefore setting it apart. It empowers users to control their data in an era of diminishing online privacy. But complete anonymity requires additional tools beyond DuckDuckGo, therefore it should be part of a broader privacy strategy. DuckDuckGo is a big deal because its robust privacy features react to prevalent tracking practices. <img alt="Tiff in Tech 使用 Tiff in Tech 的 original sound 创作的 3 categories of machine learning you should understand 💡 1. Supervised learning: The algorithm learns from labeled historical input and output data to create a model that can make predictions. Common algorithms include neural networks, decision trees, linear regression, and support vector machines. Used for tasks like sales forecasting, fraud detection, and predicting equipment failure. 2. Unsupervised learning: The algorithm finds patterns in unlabeled data to group data points into clusters. Common algorithms include Hidden Markov models, k-means, hierarchical clustering, and Gaussian mixture models. Used for customer segmentation, inventory grouping, and identifying associations in data.  3. Reinforcement learning: The algorithm learns through interaction with its environment, receiving positive or negative rewards. Common algorithms include temporal difference, deep adversarial networks, and Q-learning. Used in applications like autonomous vehicles, traffic control, and robotics, but requires high computing power. #tech #techexpert #techexplained #coding #stem #machinelearning #ai " fetchpriority="auto" decoding="async" src="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/tos-maliva-p-0068/786bfac729b14297abc5eb523fe0fc08_1714352990~tplv-dmt-logom:tos-useast2a-v-0068/o07umzmOiVx3AiXAQAEEAog8gSAFBuBzCIyfIX.image?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=uUe3NHkfu9Q7yLpZw1qMho7BCWs%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=-" imagex-type="react" imagex-version="0.3.10" srcset="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/tos-maliva-p-0068/786bfac729b14297abc5eb523fe0fc08_1714352990~tplv-dmt-logom:tos-useast2a-v-0068/o07umzmOiVx3AiXAQAEEAog8gSAFBuBzCIyfIX.image?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=uUe3NHkfu9Q7yLpZw1qMho7BCWs%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 1x, https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/tos-maliva-p-0068/786bfac729b14297abc5eb523fe0fc08_1714352990~tplv-dmt-logom:tos-useast2a-v-0068/o07umzmOiVx3AiXAQAEEAog8gSAFBuBzCIyfIX.image?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=uUe3NHkfu9Q7yLpZw1qMho7BCWs%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 2x" style="position: absolute; inset: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0px; border: none; margin: auto; display: block; width: 0px; height: 0px; min-width: 100%; max-width: 100%; min-height: 100%; max-height: 100%;">

<img alt="Tiff in Tech 使用 Tiff in Tech 的 original sound 创作的 What is a CRON job?  A cron job is a scheduled task that runs automatically at a specified time. It's commonly used to automate repetitive tasks without manual intervention. Real-world example: Generating daily sales reports 1. Write a script to:    - Retrieve sales data from the database    - Generate a formatted report    - Send the report via email    - Save a copy on the server 2. Set up a cron job to execute the script every morning at 6:00 AM:    - Edit the crontab file: `crontab -e`    - Add the line: `0 6 * * * /path/to/sales_report_script.py` 3. Save the crontab file and exit. The cron job will automatically run the script daily at 6:00 AM, generating and sending the sales report. Other common uses of cron jobs include: - Automating backups - Cleaning up log files - Sending notifications - Updating data feeds - Running maintenance tasks Cron jobs save time and effort by automating important, repetitive tasks in various domains. #tech #stem #technology #techexpert #programming " fetchpriority="auto" decoding="async" src="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/3ada5b294da345fb8c41ae830acea98c_1714173155?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=%2BNRDm4bKh9%2B8PFUlm%2BA4pMWo5m0%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=-" imagex-type="react" imagex-version="0.3.10" srcset="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/3ada5b294da345fb8c41ae830acea98c_1714173155?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=%2BNRDm4bKh9%2B8PFUlm%2BA4pMWo5m0%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 1x, https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/3ada5b294da345fb8c41ae830acea98c_1714173155?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=%2BNRDm4bKh9%2B8PFUlm%2BA4pMWo5m0%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 2x" style="position: absolute; inset: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0px; border: none; margin: auto; display: block; width: 0px; height: 0px; min-width: 100%; max-width: 100%; min-height: 100%; max-height: 100%;">

<img alt="Tiff in Tech 使用 Tiff in Tech 的 original sound 创作的 What exactly is DNS? This is something you might hear often in a tech interview or at a company you're working for. You can think of DNS like a phone book before the Internet. Just as you would use a phone book. Okay. Well, maybe we don't use phone books anymore. Our parents would use phone books to look up someone's name and phone number in the phone book. DNS helps your computer find the right website based on its domain name. When you type in. I love dogs. I mean, I know dogs are better than cats, let's face it. But regardless, when you type it in, computer doesn't actually know where to find. I love dogs dot com. It needs to translate this domain into an IP address, which is a unique numerical label that is assigned to each device connected to the internet. That's where DNS comes in. Your computer will send a request to the DNS server asking for the IP address of Isle of Dogs dot com, and the DNS server will respond with the correct IP address allowing your computer to connect to Isle of Dogs dot com website. And this process happens every single time you type in a website you want to visit. Save for your next tech interview.  #tech #technology #stem #techexpert #techexplained #stem " fetchpriority="auto" decoding="async" src="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/tos-maliva-p-0068/e25d50f942674259a9d634c9c203bb00_1713819660~tplv-dmt-logom:tos-useast2a-v-0068/okAGAfQiDBAmFAeEFmE0tUEAJCJIRIWQ7VR0AA.image?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=ja%2BjBH6qx%2BXKniSpizFCfG5JOZk%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=-" imagex-type="react" imagex-version="0.3.10" srcset="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/tos-maliva-p-0068/e25d50f942674259a9d634c9c203bb00_1713819660~tplv-dmt-logom:tos-useast2a-v-0068/okAGAfQiDBAmFAeEFmE0tUEAJCJIRIWQ7VR0AA.image?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=ja%2BjBH6qx%2BXKniSpizFCfG5JOZk%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 1x, https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/tos-maliva-p-0068/e25d50f942674259a9d634c9c203bb00_1713819660~tplv-dmt-logom:tos-useast2a-v-0068/okAGAfQiDBAmFAeEFmE0tUEAJCJIRIWQ7VR0AA.image?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=ja%2BjBH6qx%2BXKniSpizFCfG5JOZk%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 2x" style="position: absolute; inset: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0px; border: none; margin: auto; display: block; width: 0px; height: 0px; min-width: 100%; max-width: 100%; min-height: 100%; max-height: 100%;">

<img alt="Tiff in Tech 使用 Tiff in Tech 的 original sound 创作的 This is pretty cool 👇 SSL (Secure Sockets Layer) and its successor, TLS (Transport Layer Security), are cryptographic protocols that provide secure communication over the internet. They are essential for protecting sensitive information, such as passwords, credit card numbers, and personal data, as it travels between a client (like your web browser) and a server (like a website). Imagine you're sending a postcard with a sensitive message to a friend. Without a secure envelope, anyone who handles the postcard can read its contents. SSL/TLS acts like a secure envelope for your internet communication. When you visit a website with a URL that starts with &quot;https&quot; (like https://www.example.com), SSL/TLS creates an encrypted connection between your browser and the website's server. This process involves several steps: 1. The client sends a request to the server to establish a secure connection. 2. The server responds with its SSL/TLS certificate, which contains its public key and other information to verify its identity. 3. The client verifies the server's certificate and generates a unique session key. 4. The client encrypts the session key using the server's public key and sends it back to the server. 5. The server decrypts the session key using its private key, and from this point on, all communication between the client and server is encrypted using the session key. Now, any data you send or receive from the website, such as login credentials or financial information, is encrypted and unreadable to anyone who might intercept the communication. This helps protect your privacy and security online." fetchpriority="auto" decoding="async" src="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/tos-maliva-p-0068/844746d4f73b40cf82995e6b5833c0ee_1713731907~tplv-dmt-logom:tos-useast2a-v-0068/oAegiFtEEQBIQBJpXKfkSA9ARA31mDJsBAmTCA.image?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=I%2FV7U3I78Pe4uLUAe2MBSRdmPGo%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=-" imagex-type="react" imagex-version="0.3.10" srcset="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/tos-maliva-p-0068/844746d4f73b40cf82995e6b5833c0ee_1713731907~tplv-dmt-logom:tos-useast2a-v-0068/oAegiFtEEQBIQBJpXKfkSA9ARA31mDJsBAmTCA.image?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=I%2FV7U3I78Pe4uLUAe2MBSRdmPGo%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 1x, https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/tos-maliva-p-0068/844746d4f73b40cf82995e6b5833c0ee_1713731907~tplv-dmt-logom:tos-useast2a-v-0068/oAegiFtEEQBIQBJpXKfkSA9ARA31mDJsBAmTCA.image?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=I%2FV7U3I78Pe4uLUAe2MBSRdmPGo%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 2x" style="position: absolute; inset: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0px; border: none; margin: auto; display: block; width: 0px; height: 0px; min-width: 100%; max-width: 100%; min-height: 100%; max-height: 100%;">
https://www.tiktok.com/@tiffintech/video/7359691477221477637
<img alt="Tiff in Tech 使用 Danail Draganov 的 Fresh Five 创作的 What is Apples Secure Enclave?  How secure is your iPhone, really? I mean, Apple talks about the secure enclave that they use, but what really is it? Let's go through a real world example so you can always remember what Apple's secure enclave is. First off, imagine you have a high security vault in a bank and it stores valuable items like gold, rare artifacts and confidential documents. Now you can think of the secure enclave like a heavily guarded room that has the vault within it. It has its own security systems, cameras and guards that operate independently from the rest of the bank's security. So when someone wants to access items in this room, they must go through a rigorous authentication process first. And this could be through providing biometric data such as your fingerprint. Once inside, all the secure operations happen within this vault, and the guards ensure that no unauthorized person is allowed to get in. Now, here's the really cool thing. Even if someone manages to breach the bank's main security system, they still won't be able to access items in the special room because it has its own unique key and security measures. This is a real world example as to how you can think of Apple's secure enclave system works to protect your sensitive information, like your passwords, biometric information on your iPhone or iPad. #apple #tech #techtok #techexpert #techexplained " fetchpriority="auto" decoding="async" src="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/tos-maliva-p-0068/oMweQX7RQQRIAeiD3F8feClAGIykYMkxFDGNEr~tplv-dmt-logom:tos-useast2a-v-0068/oQf1A7GAXz5sEoiu4priQCpBBDAQEIIiA8EAAg.image?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=aLSk%2F%2BQ5P2EAJHOjx6I6N2QcFFk%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=-" imagex-type="react" imagex-version="0.3.10" srcset="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/tos-maliva-p-0068/oMweQX7RQQRIAeiD3F8feClAGIykYMkxFDGNEr~tplv-dmt-logom:tos-useast2a-v-0068/oQf1A7GAXz5sEoiu4priQCpBBDAQEIIiA8EAAg.image?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=aLSk%2F%2BQ5P2EAJHOjx6I6N2QcFFk%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 1x, https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/tos-maliva-p-0068/oMweQX7RQQRIAeiD3F8feClAGIykYMkxFDGNEr~tplv-dmt-logom:tos-useast2a-v-0068/oQf1A7GAXz5sEoiu4priQCpBBDAQEIIiA8EAAg.image?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=aLSk%2F%2BQ5P2EAJHOjx6I6N2QcFFk%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 2x" style="position: absolute; inset: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0px; border: none; margin: auto; display: block; width: 0px; height: 0px; min-width: 100%; max-width: 100%; min-height: 100%; max-height: 100%;">

<img alt="Tiff in Tech 使用 Tiff in Tech 的 original sound 创作的 Fully generated AI videos using 1 image🤯 Microsoft just shared about their new AI framework called VASA-1. <img alt="Tiff in Tech 使用 Tiff in Tech 的 original sound 创作的 How does Spotify recommendations algorithm work?  Spotify employs a complex system of machine learning algorithms and data analysis to provide personalized music recommendations to its users. Here's an overview of the key components and techniques used in Spotify's recommendation system: 1. Collaborative Filtering:    - Spotify uses collaborative filtering to identify patterns and similarities in user behavior and preferences.    - It analyzes user-item interactions, such as liked songs, playlists, and listening history, to find users with similar tastes.    - By identifying similar users, Spotify can recommend songs that those users have enjoyed but the current user hasn't discovered yet. 2. Content-Based Filtering:    - Spotify also employs content-based filtering, which focuses on the characteristics and features of the songs themselves.    - It analyzes various audio features like tempo, key, loudness, danceability, and more to understand the musical attributes of each track.    - By comparing the audio features of songs, Spotify can recommend tracks with similar characteristics to the ones a user has enjoyed. 3. Natural Language Processing (NLP):    - Spotify uses NLP techniques to process and understand user-generated text data, such as playlist titles, descriptions, and user reviews.    - By analyzing the semantic meaning and context of the text, Spotify can extract insights about the genre, mood, or theme of the music.    - This information is used to enhance the recommendation process by considering the contextual aspects of the music. 4. Deep Learning and Neural Networks:    - Spotify employs deep learning techniques, particularly neural networks, to learn complex patterns and representations from the vast amount of user and music data.    - Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs) and Recurrent Neural Networks (RNNs) are used to process audio data and capture temporal dependencies in music.    - These deep learning models enable Spotify to generate more nuanced and contextually relevant recommendations. 5. Ensemble Methods:    - Spotify combines multiple recommendation algorithms and models to generate more accurate and diverse recommendations.    - Ensemble methods, such as weighted averaging or ranking aggregation, are used to combine the outputs of different models.    - By leveraging the strengths of various algorithms, Spotify can provide more robust and personalized recommendations. #tech #techexplained #technology #stem " fetchpriority="auto" decoding="async" src="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/tos-maliva-p-0068/oEUQYBuIRhSHEkAZ0RIS1AipGvQEE0gy5iB7B~tplv-dmt-logom:tos-useast2a-v-0068/oEARDEQYI1mAuqEhQCjA3JFAKEIfSBfasmAuUN.image?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=y2W%2FKYOuvAVzbbyX68DsRDqQmEI%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=-" imagex-type="react" imagex-version="0.3.10" srcset="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/tos-maliva-p-0068/oEUQYBuIRhSHEkAZ0RIS1AipGvQEE0gy5iB7B~tplv-dmt-logom:tos-useast2a-v-0068/oEARDEQYI1mAuqEhQCjA3JFAKEIfSBfasmAuUN.image?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=y2W%2FKYOuvAVzbbyX68DsRDqQmEI%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 1x, https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/tos-maliva-p-0068/oEUQYBuIRhSHEkAZ0RIS1AipGvQEE0gy5iB7B~tplv-dmt-logom:tos-useast2a-v-0068/oEARDEQYI1mAuqEhQCjA3JFAKEIfSBfasmAuUN.image?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=y2W%2FKYOuvAVzbbyX68DsRDqQmEI%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 2x" style="position: absolute; inset: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0px; border: none; margin: auto; display: block; width: 0px; height: 0px; min-width: 100%; max-width: 100%; min-height: 100%; max-height: 100%;">

<img alt="Tiff in Tech 使用 Tiff in Tech 的 original sound 创作的 Does using Tor Browser make you completely anonymous online?  It's a myth that most people think using Tor browser will make you totally anonymous online, when in reality there are a lot of exceptions to this. If you're not familiar with Tor browser, it is considered to be the most private browser out there to keep you anonymous when you're going online. But here's where it gets interesting. There are a few exceptions to stay anonymous when using Tor. Let's start with the obvious one. If you are logged in to your personal accounts on Tor, your identity can still be tied to your browsing session. Now here's another way that Tor might not be as secure as you think. Obviously, what computer you are using Tor on. If this computer is infected with malware or Keyloggers, your actions can still be monitor rendering tor to become useless. Now, many assume that Tor completely protects your identity, which makes your guard go down. Now, while Tor is a really great privacy tool, it is definitely not perfect, and it's very important to be aware of that. For more tech tips.  #tech #techtips #stem #technology " fetchpriority="auto" decoding="async" src="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/oQTn3uUtBIoSDNz4AUiBkrId5AfTzAgEiLojCB?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=btdI%2BLZanS%2BXpBPp8S8DcsWoxMI%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=-" imagex-type="react" imagex-version="0.3.10" srcset="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/oQTn3uUtBIoSDNz4AUiBkrId5AfTzAgEiLojCB?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=btdI%2BLZanS%2BXpBPp8S8DcsWoxMI%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 1x, https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/oQTn3uUtBIoSDNz4AUiBkrId5AfTzAgEiLojCB?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=btdI%2BLZanS%2BXpBPp8S8DcsWoxMI%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 2x" style="position: absolute; inset: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0px; border: none; margin: auto; display: block; width: 0px; height: 0px; min-width: 100%; max-width: 100%; min-height: 100%; max-height: 100%;">

<img alt="Tiff in Tech 使用 Tiff in Tech 的 original sound 创作的 Have you ever wondered how does the Internet work?  I mean, like actually work? That's a pretty big question, but we're going to answer it. Let's start with the basics. Let's start with computers and devices. Of course, each computer and device has its own IP address, which is like a home address. But for the Internet and these devices are connected to the Internet through various ways. Then we have our ISP, or better known as Internet service providers. And all you need to know about this is these are the companies that give you access to the Internet. Why you pay them all the money, and it's your ISP that gives your device its IP address. So when you go to a website, your device sends a request over the Internet, and this request is broken down into small packets of data, each tagged with the IP address of your device. And these packets travel through various routers and switches which are in charge of directing the traffic efficiently. And eventually these packets reach the server hosting the website you want to visit. Then they need to turn around. This is the return journey. So the packets then after they've gone in the data for the website you want to visit, for example, make their way back to your device and they might follow a different path for this. And through this process, various protocols work smoothly or like hopefully they do whatever happens in a matter of seconds. #tech #techexpert #techexplained #stem #howdoestheinternetwork " fetchpriority="auto" decoding="async" src="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/tos-maliva-p-0068/ooJxjOsZLISdIZChyCeFOXXEQ6DCtqA9Lgf3fB~tplv-dmt-logom:tos-useast2a-v-0068/owx11A2IjQdAfStfyHIAIQDLA1WFEC7OEgnXye.image?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=mR%2Fq%2FiDG%2Fw%2BDlXbeFCaiPyfaM%2B8%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=-" imagex-type="react" imagex-version="0.3.10" srcset="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/tos-maliva-p-0068/ooJxjOsZLISdIZChyCeFOXXEQ6DCtqA9Lgf3fB~tplv-dmt-logom:tos-useast2a-v-0068/owx11A2IjQdAfStfyHIAIQDLA1WFEC7OEgnXye.image?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=mR%2Fq%2FiDG%2Fw%2BDlXbeFCaiPyfaM%2B8%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 1x, https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/tos-maliva-p-0068/ooJxjOsZLISdIZChyCeFOXXEQ6DCtqA9Lgf3fB~tplv-dmt-logom:tos-useast2a-v-0068/owx11A2IjQdAfStfyHIAIQDLA1WFEC7OEgnXye.image?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=mR%2Fq%2FiDG%2Fw%2BDlXbeFCaiPyfaM%2B8%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 2x" style="position: absolute; inset: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0px; border: none; margin: auto; display: block; width: 0px; height: 0px; min-width: 100%; max-width: 100%; min-height: 100%; max-height: 100%;">

<img alt="Tiff in Tech 使用 Tiff in Tech 的 original sound 创作的 Meet Devin, the world’s first fully autonomous AI software engineer. ‍ Devin is a tireless, skilled teammate, equally ready to build alongside you or independently complete tasks for you to review. With Devin, engineers can focus on more interesting problems and engineering teams can strive for more ambitious goals. Devin's Capabilities With advances in long-term reasoning and planning, Devin can plan and execute complex engineering tasks requiring thousands of decisions. Devin can recall relevant context at every step, learn over time, and fix mistakes.  Devin is equipped with common developer tools including the shell, code editor, and browser within a sandboxed compute environment—everything a human would need to do their work. Finally, Devin has the ability to actively collaborate with the user. Devin reports on its progress in real time, accepts feedback, and works together with you through design choices as needed. #tech #ai #devin " fetchpriority="auto" decoding="async" src="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/ooEfA7dxPLfuYReEQXIG27ekgU0MA24uFkj75G?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=S6v6Rw%2Bon4XvUHzpYMKpxZJDdMw%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=-" imagex-type="react" imagex-version="0.3.10" srcset="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/ooEfA7dxPLfuYReEQXIG27ekgU0MA24uFkj75G?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=S6v6Rw%2Bon4XvUHzpYMKpxZJDdMw%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 1x, https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/ooEfA7dxPLfuYReEQXIG27ekgU0MA24uFkj75G?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=S6v6Rw%2Bon4XvUHzpYMKpxZJDdMw%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 2x" style="position: absolute; inset: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0px; border: none; margin: auto; display: block; width: 0px; height: 0px; min-width: 100%; max-width: 100%; min-height: 100%; max-height: 100%;">

<img alt="Tiff in Tech 使用 Tiff in Tech 的 original sound 创作的 Come study machine learning with me A decision tree is like a flowchart that helps in making decisions based on yes/no questions. Imagine you're trying to decide what to wear today, and you have a decision tree to help you out. The tree starts at the root (the top) with a question about the weather.  - If it's raining (yes), the tree might tell you to wear a raincoat.  - If it's not raining (no), it asks another question, maybe about whether it's cold or not. Each time you answer a question, you follow the path down the tree that matches your answer, leading to new questions or to the end of the tree, where it tells you what to do (like wearing shorts if it's sunny and warm). In more technical terms, a decision tree is used in data science to help predict an outcome based on past data. It asks a series of true/false questions about the data (like is it raining, is it cold), and each question helps it get closer to predicting the outcome (like predicting if you should wear a coat or not). The decision tree makes these predictions by learning from examples (past data) and figuring out which questions are the best to ask and in what order. However, if the tree asks too many specific questions, it might get too focused on the examples it learned from and not be good at making predictions about new situations. So, sometimes it's necessary to simplify the tree to make it more useful for predicting new things. #tech #techexpert #futuretech " fetchpriority="auto" decoding="async" src="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/osVfjFxgARCRDDnfIlPBl2I0XwEE7lzJQBBuEr?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=0%2BnoccBYCZU8zVKzPy%2Bv9m5xGXg%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=-" imagex-type="react" imagex-version="0.3.10" srcset="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/osVfjFxgARCRDDnfIlPBl2I0XwEE7lzJQBBuEr?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=0%2BnoccBYCZU8zVKzPy%2Bv9m5xGXg%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 1x, https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/osVfjFxgARCRDDnfIlPBl2I0XwEE7lzJQBBuEr?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=0%2BnoccBYCZU8zVKzPy%2Bv9m5xGXg%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 2x" style="position: absolute; inset: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0px; border: none; margin: auto; display: block; width: 0px; height: 0px; min-width: 100%; max-width: 100%; min-height: 100%; max-height: 100%;">

<img alt="Tiff in Tech 使用 Tiff in Tech 的 original sound 创作的 How can you tell if public Wi-Fi is safe?  When using public Wi-Fi, ensure it's secure to protect your data. Here's how: Seek Encryption: Opt for networks with WPA2 or WPA3 encryption, indicated by a required connection password. Verify the Network: Ensure you're connecting to an official network. Confirm the network name with an employee if unsure. Use a VPN: A Virtual Private Network encrypts your data, safeguarding your online activities from others on the network. Enable Firewall: Activate your device's firewall to monitor and protect against unauthorized access. <img alt="Tiff in Tech 使用 Tiff in Tech 的 original sound 创作的 How ChatGPT work technically?  Large Language Models (LLMs) like GPT are sophisticated systems designed to process and generate language, comprised of several key components: Training Data: The extensive collection of text (books, articles, websites) from which the model learns language patterns, styles, and context. Tokenization: Breaking down text into smaller pieces (tokens) for the model to process. It’s like preparing ingredients for cooking. Embeddings: Converting tokens into numerical values to help the model understand word meanings and relationships. Think of it as giving each word a unique numerical fingerprint. Transformer Architecture: The core technology that allows the model to understand context and generate text. It includes: Attention Mechanism: Helps the model focus on relevant parts of the text to produce coherent and context-aware responses. Pre-training and Fine-tuning: Pre-training: The broad learning phase where the model learns from its large dataset. Fine-tuning: Adjusting the model for specific tasks by training it on more targeted data. Output Layer: The component that translates the model's processed information back into human-readable text, whether it's answering questions, completing prompts, or creating content. Decoding Strategies: Techniques the model uses to select the most appropriate words for generating coherent and relevant text. #tech #education #stem #ai #artificialintelligence #chatgpt " fetchpriority="auto" decoding="async" src="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/tos-maliva-p-0068/oA9A4AiTmVBCI6otD7ALiOqgfzkBryICYxETIt~tplv-dmt-logom:tos-useast2a-v-0068/ogBUkxJEAdRbAQmIeCFlAxHDQoJQABkMfm6Eop.image?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=5FkzehNgE3DRMclmI8sBpqoTcyY%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=-" imagex-type="react" imagex-version="0.3.10" srcset="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/tos-maliva-p-0068/oA9A4AiTmVBCI6otD7ALiOqgfzkBryICYxETIt~tplv-dmt-logom:tos-useast2a-v-0068/ogBUkxJEAdRbAQmIeCFlAxHDQoJQABkMfm6Eop.image?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=5FkzehNgE3DRMclmI8sBpqoTcyY%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 1x, https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/tos-maliva-p-0068/oA9A4AiTmVBCI6otD7ALiOqgfzkBryICYxETIt~tplv-dmt-logom:tos-useast2a-v-0068/ogBUkxJEAdRbAQmIeCFlAxHDQoJQABkMfm6Eop.image?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=5FkzehNgE3DRMclmI8sBpqoTcyY%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 2x" style="position: absolute; inset: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0px; border: none; margin: auto; display: block; width: 0px; height: 0px; min-width: 100%; max-width: 100%; min-height: 100%; max-height: 100%;">

<img alt="Tiff in Tech 使用 Tiff in Tech 的 original sound 创作的 Can cell phones cause explosions at gas stations? The belief that cell phones can cause explosions at gas stations is a myth. Scientific evidence and research have shown that cell phones do not produce enough energy to ignite gasoline vapors. Regulatory bodies and safety organizations, including the FCC and the Petroleum Equipment Institute, confirm there's no evidence linking cell phones to gas station fires or explosions. The real risk comes from static electricity discharge, not mobile phones. While safety warnings exist, they're precautionary measures against potential risks and distractions, not based on incidents caused by cell phones. #tech #technology " fetchpriority="auto" decoding="async" src="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/ooer6RDveXhuIAIpe0YLfRyGEXSWkQGJ8vkACF?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=0JD5%2FoWk%2FWtgkaJkFch%2FhzX09Uo%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=-" imagex-type="react" imagex-version="0.3.10" srcset="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/ooer6RDveXhuIAIpe0YLfRyGEXSWkQGJ8vkACF?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=0JD5%2FoWk%2FWtgkaJkFch%2FhzX09Uo%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 1x, https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/ooer6RDveXhuIAIpe0YLfRyGEXSWkQGJ8vkACF?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=0JD5%2FoWk%2FWtgkaJkFch%2FhzX09Uo%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 2x" style="position: absolute; inset: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0px; border: none; margin: auto; display: block; width: 0px; height: 0px; min-width: 100%; max-width: 100%; min-height: 100%; max-height: 100%;">

<img alt="Tiff in Tech 使用 Tiff in Tech 的 original sound 创作的 Are you team dark mode or light mode?! Benefits of Light Mode on the Eyes: ➡️Enhanced Readability in Well-Lit Conditions: Bright backgrounds with dark text (classic light mode) can offer better readability in brightly lit environments or during the day. ➡️Reduced Pupil Dilation: Light mode causes the pupils to constrict, which can result in sharper vision and potentially less strain when focusing on detailed tasks. ➡️Optimal for Detailed Work: High contrast of dark text on a light background is generally preferred for tasks requiring focus and attention to detail. Benefits of Dark Mode on the Eyes: ➡️Reduced Glare in Low-Light Conditions: Dark mode can decrease screen glare when using devices in darker environments, leading to less eye strain. ➡️Lower Blue Light Exposure: May reduce exposure to blue light, which is linked to sleep disturbances, making it beneficial before bedtime. ➡️Potential Relief for Light Sensitivity: Individuals with photophobia or light sensitivity might find dark mode more comfortable for extended screen use. Each mode offers distinct advantages depending on the user's environment, time of day, and specific visual needs. Switching between modes based on these factors can help maximize comfort and minimize eye strain. #tech #technology #techexplained #techexpert " fetchpriority="auto" decoding="async" src="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/1ea252c6b1dd49e0a69860a849f0d7ae_1709326795?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=lVoX1gv%2FOxqehUmq9%2Bs7nCDPKBA%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=-" imagex-type="react" imagex-version="0.3.10" srcset="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/1ea252c6b1dd49e0a69860a849f0d7ae_1709326795?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=lVoX1gv%2FOxqehUmq9%2Bs7nCDPKBA%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 1x, https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/1ea252c6b1dd49e0a69860a849f0d7ae_1709326795?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=lVoX1gv%2FOxqehUmq9%2Bs7nCDPKBA%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 2x" style="position: absolute; inset: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0px; border: none; margin: auto; display: block; width: 0px; height: 0px; min-width: 100%; max-width: 100%; min-height: 100%; max-height: 100%;">

<img alt="Tiff in Tech 使用 Tiff in Tech 的 original sound 创作的 Is generative AI going to be the end of coding? Speaking at the recent World Government Summit in Dubai, Jensen, president and co-founder of NVIDIA shared: &quot;It is our job to create computing technology such that nobody has to program. And that the programming language is human,&quot; said the CEO. &quot;Everybody in the world is now a programmer. <img alt="Tiff in Tech 使用 Tiff in Tech 的 original sound 创作的 How does live straming actually work?!  Real-time live streaming on platforms like YouTube involves capturing video and audio content, compressing and encoding it in a streamable format almost instantaneously, and then transmitting it over the internet to viewers in near real-time.  This process employs protocols like Real-Time Messaging Protocol (RTMP) or HTTP Live Streaming (HLS) to manage the delivery of live content.  Adaptive bitrate streaming (ABS) is also crucial, adjusting the stream quality in real-time based on each viewer's network speed and device performance to minimize buffering and ensure a smooth viewing experience.  Behind the scenes, distributed content delivery networks (CDNs) play a vital role in reducing latency by caching streams on edge servers closer to the audience, enhancing the scalability and reliability of live streaming services. #tech #techexpert #stem " fetchpriority="auto" decoding="async" src="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/e358ed1d90a24f3584d6c1951df582d7_1708546249?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=gh7m%2B657b9ppiKikOdDUDFVxMPk%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=-" imagex-type="react" imagex-version="0.3.10" srcset="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/e358ed1d90a24f3584d6c1951df582d7_1708546249?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=gh7m%2B657b9ppiKikOdDUDFVxMPk%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 1x, https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/e358ed1d90a24f3584d6c1951df582d7_1708546249?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=gh7m%2B657b9ppiKikOdDUDFVxMPk%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 2x" style="position: absolute; inset: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0px; border: none; margin: auto; display: block; width: 0px; height: 0px; min-width: 100%; max-width: 100%; min-height: 100%; max-height: 100%;">

<img alt="Tiff in Tech 使用 Tiff in Tech 的 original sound 创作的 Why is WhatsApp considered the most secure messaging app?  It's used by billions of people worldwide, raising the question of how it maintains the security of everyone's messages. WhatsApp employs several methods to ensure user security. While it is regarded by some as the most secure messaging app, how does it achieve this? Moreover, how feasible is it to intercept these messages? When you send a message to your friend via WhatsApp, it utilizes end-to-end encryption. This means your messages are encrypted with a unique lock on your device before they are even sent over the internet and can only be decrypted by the recipient's device. But how does the recipient's device know how to decrypt the message?  This begins when two users start a conversation; their devices perform a digital handshake, securely exchanging cryptographic keys through a process known as the Diffie-Hellman key exchange. What's important to understand is that this process ensures both parties have the necessary keys to encrypt and decrypt messages, but these keys are never exposed to WhatsApp or any other third party. So, how difficult would it be to intercept WhatsApp messages? From a theoretical standpoint, with unlimited resources, time, and the future development of powerful quantum computers, it might be possible to crack the encryption. However, in practical terms, with current technology, it is virtually impossible to intercept and decrypt messages without access to the private keys, which are securely stored on the devices of the communicating parties. #tech #techexplained #techexpert #stem " fetchpriority="auto" decoding="async" src="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/56ac9dfdc302431d967bab8a4c630856_1707956679?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=6mhkyCO%2BOKxQvDMKP209%2FR14jW8%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=-" imagex-type="react" imagex-version="0.3.10" srcset="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/56ac9dfdc302431d967bab8a4c630856_1707956679?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=6mhkyCO%2BOKxQvDMKP209%2FR14jW8%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 1x, https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/56ac9dfdc302431d967bab8a4c630856_1707956679?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=6mhkyCO%2BOKxQvDMKP209%2FR14jW8%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 2x" style="position: absolute; inset: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0px; border: none; margin: auto; display: block; width: 0px; height: 0px; min-width: 100%; max-width: 100%; min-height: 100%; max-height: 100%;">

<img alt="Tiff in Tech 使用 Tiff in Tech 的 original sound 创作的 AI/ML concepts/tools I learned about in my first class 👇 Anaconda Navigator and Jupyter Notebook are popular tools among data scientists, developers, and researchers for managing projects and performing data analysis. 🤖Anaconda Navigator Anaconda Navigator is a graphical user interface (GUI) included with the Anaconda distribution, which is a popular Python distribution used for scientific computing. Navigator provides a user-friendly way to launch applications included with Anaconda without needing to use command-line instructions. It's designed to make it easier to manage your Anaconda environment and the various packages, libraries, and tools that come with it. Managing Environments: You can create, export, list, remove, and update environments that have different versions of Python and/or packages installed. Launching Applications: Navigator allows you to launch applications included with Anaconda, such as Jupyter Notebooks, JupyterLab, Spyder (an IDE for Python), RStudio (if you have R installed), and others, with just a click. Managing Packages: It provides a graphical interface for installing, updating, and uninstalling Python packages. This can be especially helpful for those who prefer not to use the command line. 💻Jupyter Notebook Jupyter Notebook is an open-source web application that allows you to create and share documents that contain live code, equations, visualizations, and narrative text. It's part of the Project Jupyter and is widely used for data cleaning and transformation, numerical simulation, statistical modeling, data visualization, machine learning, and much more.  Interactive Computing: Jupyter Notebooks provide an interactive environment where you can execute code in a step-by-step manner and see immediate results. This is great for exploratory analysis and experimenting with code. #tech #ai #artificialintelligence #coding #python " fetchpriority="auto" decoding="async" src="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/owqvw0AggPYAXIetfJJRcueAWOfKMiEuQCif4q?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=TVmwhnwMxAVzT92HJsnHd15zlzc%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=-" imagex-type="react" imagex-version="0.3.10" srcset="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/owqvw0AggPYAXIetfJJRcueAWOfKMiEuQCif4q?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=TVmwhnwMxAVzT92HJsnHd15zlzc%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 1x, https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/owqvw0AggPYAXIetfJJRcueAWOfKMiEuQCif4q?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=TVmwhnwMxAVzT92HJsnHd15zlzc%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 2x" style="position: absolute; inset: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0px; border: none; margin: auto; display: block; width: 0px; height: 0px; min-width: 100%; max-width: 100%; min-height: 100%; max-height: 100%;">

<img alt="Tiff in Tech 使用 Tiff in Tech 的 original sound 创作的 Netflix uses Chaos Engineering, specifically through their tool known as Chaos Monkey, to enhance the resilience and reliability of their systems, ensuring a seamless streaming experience for users worldwide. Chaos Engineering involves injecting controlled chaos into systems to identify and address potential weaknesses. Chaos Monkey plays a central role in this process by randomly terminating instances in Netflix's production environment. This simulation of real-world failures allows engineers to observe how systems respond and to improve fault tolerance. By embracing the unpredictability of failures, Netflix engineers are able to strengthen their architecture, ensuring that it can handle disruptions gracefully and maintain uninterrupted service for users. This approach to system design not only improves reliability but also prepares the infrastructure to withstand and quickly recover from unforeseen challenges. #ai #stem #tech #techexplained " fetchpriority="auto" decoding="async" src="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/o4gjglEXfABYBeDWEmnFHtIQXFRnYxlVPJEEBU?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=AhEMQliAxOBPb%2BB%2FtcFVzvkDkU8%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=-" imagex-type="react" imagex-version="0.3.10" srcset="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/o4gjglEXfABYBeDWEmnFHtIQXFRnYxlVPJEEBU?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=AhEMQliAxOBPb%2BB%2FtcFVzvkDkU8%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 1x, https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/o4gjglEXfABYBeDWEmnFHtIQXFRnYxlVPJEEBU?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=AhEMQliAxOBPb%2BB%2FtcFVzvkDkU8%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 2x" style="position: absolute; inset: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0px; border: none; margin: auto; display: block; width: 0px; height: 0px; min-width: 100%; max-width: 100%; min-height: 100%; max-height: 100%;">

<img alt="Tiff in Tech 使用 Zen music 的 Content Music Background (Live) 创作的 How does the blockchain actually work?  Implementing blockchain in the supply chain, like tracing coffee beans from farm to shop, involves assigning a unique digital identity to each batch, recording every transaction as a block on the blockchain, and linking these blocks to form a chain. This process is secured through decentralized verification by network participants, ensuring that each transaction is valid and making the ledger immutable. The blockchain can be public for transparency or permissioned for privacy, allowing stakeholders to trace the product's journey securely and efficiently. Additionally, smart contracts automate transactions, such as payments, once certain conditions are met, reducing the need for intermediaries and streamlining the supply chain process. This system enhances trust among consumers and operational efficiencies for businesses. #tech #stem #techexplained " fetchpriority="auto" decoding="async" src="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/tos-maliva-p-0068/oIvBo0ZVJKQ3EUSBxFDZrCdBFijAcBHiIEzNF~tplv-dmt-logom:tos-useast2a-v-0068/oABvc3QZA0AdcqOTBLERAQHD6Izii64AUBEFi.image?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=O4shbxww5BeWGMOh8J4JlLEd6%2FI%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=-" imagex-type="react" imagex-version="0.3.10" srcset="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/tos-maliva-p-0068/oIvBo0ZVJKQ3EUSBxFDZrCdBFijAcBHiIEzNF~tplv-dmt-logom:tos-useast2a-v-0068/oABvc3QZA0AdcqOTBLERAQHD6Izii64AUBEFi.image?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=O4shbxww5BeWGMOh8J4JlLEd6%2FI%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 1x, https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/tos-maliva-p-0068/oIvBo0ZVJKQ3EUSBxFDZrCdBFijAcBHiIEzNF~tplv-dmt-logom:tos-useast2a-v-0068/oABvc3QZA0AdcqOTBLERAQHD6Izii64AUBEFi.image?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=O4shbxww5BeWGMOh8J4JlLEd6%2FI%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 2x" style="position: absolute; inset: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0px; border: none; margin: auto; display: block; width: 0px; height: 0px; min-width: 100%; max-width: 100%; min-height: 100%; max-height: 100%;">

<img alt="Tiff in Tech 使用 Tiff in Tech 的 original sound 创作的 What exactly is Big-O notation?!  Big-O notation might sound a bit technical, but it's really just a way to describe how fast a computer algorithm works, kind of like a speedometer for code. Let's use the example of looking for a name in a phone book. If the phone book isn't sorted and you have to go through each name one by one, this is like a linear search, or O(n). It's straightforward but gets slower as the phone book gets bigger. Now, if the phone book is sorted, you can use a smarter method called binary search, or O(log n), where you keep cutting the list in half. It's like playing a clever game of 'hot and cold' and gets you to the right name much faster, especially in a really big phone book. And finally, if you just need to pick out the very first name in the phone book, that’s a constant time operation, or O(1) - super quick and the size of the phone book doesn’t matter. Big-O notation is a handy way to talk about these different scenarios and understand why some methods are quicker than others, especially when you're dealing with a lot of data. #tech #bigo #technology #stem " fetchpriority="auto" decoding="async" src="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/ca81ee9d3d784584a39ef8bd8cd383db_1706659464?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=%2FpZ5TCfj3yIazWfn8hi%2B2Tfq07Q%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=-" imagex-type="react" imagex-version="0.3.10" srcset="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/ca81ee9d3d784584a39ef8bd8cd383db_1706659464?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=%2FpZ5TCfj3yIazWfn8hi%2B2Tfq07Q%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 1x, https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/ca81ee9d3d784584a39ef8bd8cd383db_1706659464?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=%2FpZ5TCfj3yIazWfn8hi%2B2Tfq07Q%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 2x" style="position: absolute; inset: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0px; border: none; margin: auto; display: block; width: 0px; height: 0px; min-width: 100%; max-width: 100%; min-height: 100%; max-height: 100%;">

<img alt="Tiff in Tech 使用 Pavel 的 Hip Hop Background(814204) 创作的 How many jobs will be replaced by AI? And how many new ones will be created? <img alt="Tiff in Tech 使用 Tiff in Tech 的 original sound 创作的 How does ChatGPT technically work? When receiving user input, it undergoes preprocessing and tokenization to convert text into a machine-readable format. These tokens are then embedded into vectors and processed by the transformer neural network, which uses mechanisms to understand contextual nuances.  With ChatGPT, a large aspect of its functionality is Reinforcement Learning from Human Feedback (RLHF), where it's fine-tuned with human input to ensure the responses are not only contextually appropriate but also aligned with being helpful, truthful, and harmless. This helps ChatGPT to provide responses that are coherent and contextually relevant.  #tech #technology #techexplainers #techtok #ai #artificial_intelligence " fetchpriority="auto" decoding="async" src="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/tos-maliva-p-0068/owIIWFLatIGf7hCAGeCgeiIhLrQSjAuCSqBwBC~tplv-dmt-logom:tos-useast2a-v-0068/oowrRYsilIJAEABlBCtFAFIEQHDAtMA5JQfeBC.image?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=%2By5X8bPvyMiW%2BrKNbvV49NbX4y8%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=-" imagex-type="react" imagex-version="0.3.10" srcset="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/tos-maliva-p-0068/owIIWFLatIGf7hCAGeCgeiIhLrQSjAuCSqBwBC~tplv-dmt-logom:tos-useast2a-v-0068/oowrRYsilIJAEABlBCtFAFIEQHDAtMA5JQfeBC.image?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=%2By5X8bPvyMiW%2BrKNbvV49NbX4y8%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 1x, https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/tos-maliva-p-0068/owIIWFLatIGf7hCAGeCgeiIhLrQSjAuCSqBwBC~tplv-dmt-logom:tos-useast2a-v-0068/oowrRYsilIJAEABlBCtFAFIEQHDAtMA5JQfeBC.image?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=%2By5X8bPvyMiW%2BrKNbvV49NbX4y8%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 2x" style="position: absolute; inset: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0px; border: none; margin: auto; display: block; width: 0px; height: 0px; min-width: 100%; max-width: 100%; min-height: 100%; max-height: 100%;">

<img alt="Tiff in Tech 使用 Tiff in Tech 的 original sound 创作的 Do you really nees to switch your phone to airplane mode during a flight?!  When you activate airplane mode, or flight mode, on your phone, it turns off wireless and cellular signals to prevent interference with aircraft systems, as recommended by the FAA. In this mode, you can still manually enable Wi-Fi and Bluetooth if your plane and airline allow it. If you don't use airplane mode, your phone's radio transmissions could interfere with the plane's communication and navigation, especially during critical phases like reduced-visibility landings. While you could technically make cellular calls at lower altitudes, the FCC prohibits this in the U.S. when airborne. Regulations vary internationally, with the EU recently approving 5G use on planes, differing from U.S. restrictions due to variations in technology and safety considerations. #technology #tech " fetchpriority="auto" decoding="async" src="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/oIACriLhDSjdIHaIL0Ad1IQGjgTSYR6CecefSg?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=4jD%2B5ICD8vQRPWPARE5CkTNGk%2Fg%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=-" imagex-type="react" imagex-version="0.3.10" srcset="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/oIACriLhDSjdIHaIL0Ad1IQGjgTSYR6CecefSg?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=4jD%2B5ICD8vQRPWPARE5CkTNGk%2Fg%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 1x, https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/oIACriLhDSjdIHaIL0Ad1IQGjgTSYR6CecefSg?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=4jD%2B5ICD8vQRPWPARE5CkTNGk%2Fg%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 2x" style="position: absolute; inset: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0px; border: none; margin: auto; display: block; width: 0px; height: 0px; min-width: 100%; max-width: 100%; min-height: 100%; max-height: 100%;">

<img alt="Tiff in Tech 使用 Tiff in Tech 的 original sound 创作的 Is your phone actually listening to you?  Here is how you can block third party cookies.  On your computer, open Chrome. At the top right, click More More and then Settings Settings. Click Privacy and security and then Third-party cookies. Select an option: -Allow third-party cookies. -Block third-party cookies in -Incognito mode. Block third-party cookies. If you block third-party cookies, all third-party cookies from other sites are blocked unless the site is allowed on your exceptions list. When you search for something on Google, the information is often tracked using cookies and shared across various advertising networks, including those used by social media platforms. This shared data allows social media sites to display ads relevant to your recent searches, utilizing sophisticated algorithms for targeted advertising. To help prevent this, you can use privacy-focused browsers like Firefox or Brave, which offer enhanced privacy settings to limit tracking. Adjusting your browser settings to block third-party cookies, regularly clearing your cookies, and using incognito or private browsing modes can also reduce tracking. Additionally, installing ad-blocking and anti-tracking extensions like uBlock Origin or Privacy Badger can help. Opting out of targeted advertising through tools provided by the Digital Advertising Alliance or the Network Advertising Initiative can further limit ad targeting based on your online activity. These measures can enhance your online privacy and reduce the likelihood of seeing ads on social media based on your Google searches. #tech #technology #techexpert #techexplained " fetchpriority="auto" decoding="async" src="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/df58439bd46e43d2ab022ece10514d3f_1705705082?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=8aHIdFvUkCQ8N%2BECgKDdqiBTfYY%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=-" imagex-type="react" imagex-version="0.3.10" srcset="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/df58439bd46e43d2ab022ece10514d3f_1705705082?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=8aHIdFvUkCQ8N%2BECgKDdqiBTfYY%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 1x, https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/df58439bd46e43d2ab022ece10514d3f_1705705082?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=8aHIdFvUkCQ8N%2BECgKDdqiBTfYY%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 2x" style="position: absolute; inset: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0px; border: none; margin: auto; display: block; width: 0px; height: 0px; min-width: 100%; max-width: 100%; min-height: 100%; max-height: 100%;">
