<img alt="Tiff in Tech 使用 Tiff in Tech 的 original sound 创作的 Why are keyboards not in alphabetical order?  There is another theory than the video that suggests the QWERTY keyboard layout was influenced by this The theory suggests that the QWERTY keyboard was influenced by Morse code. While the theory about reducing typewriter jams is widely accepted, some historians have proposed that Morse code played a role in shaping the arrangement of keys. According to this theory, Christopher Sholes, the inventor of the typewriter and the QWERTY layout, may have been inspired by Morse code when designing the keyboard. Morse code is a system of representing letters and numbers using combinations of dots and dashes, and it was well-known during the time when the typewriter was being developed. Some argue that Sholes may have organized the keys to make typing Morse code more efficient, as early telegraph operators were required to have a good understanding of Morse code. #tech #techexplained #techexpert " fetchpriority="auto" decoding="async" src="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/tos-maliva-p-0068/oMWmBf7eDB2lFqOEilExccErpBJIPcWQyoRGYA~tplv-dmt-logom:tos-useast2a-v-0068/o4IIt1BdEiANIxB0vAiEAxCAg5uOfIGlyLrCo3.image?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=w2hSS%2BTkRQneAthgIWJ4y069kHA%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=-" imagex-type="react" imagex-version="0.3.10" srcset="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/tos-maliva-p-0068/oMWmBf7eDB2lFqOEilExccErpBJIPcWQyoRGYA~tplv-dmt-logom:tos-useast2a-v-0068/o4IIt1BdEiANIxB0vAiEAxCAg5uOfIGlyLrCo3.image?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=w2hSS%2BTkRQneAthgIWJ4y069kHA%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 1x, https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/tos-maliva-p-0068/oMWmBf7eDB2lFqOEilExccErpBJIPcWQyoRGYA~tplv-dmt-logom:tos-useast2a-v-0068/o4IIt1BdEiANIxB0vAiEAxCAg5uOfIGlyLrCo3.image?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=w2hSS%2BTkRQneAthgIWJ4y069kHA%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 2x" style="position: absolute; inset: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0px; border: none; margin: auto; display: block; width: 0px; height: 0px; min-width: 100%; max-width: 100%; min-height: 100%; max-height: 100%;">

<img alt="Tiff in Tech 使用 Tiff in Tech 的 original sound 创作的 How dangerous is public Wi-Fi? And how can you protect yourself? Here are a few ways to help protect yourself  Use a VPN: A virtual private network encrypts your data, making it much more difficult for hackers to intercept. Choose a reputable VPN provider with a strong encryption protocol. Avoid sending sensitive information: If you need to access sensitive information, such as your bank account or online accounts, do so from a secure network, such as your home Wi-Fi. <img alt="Tiff in Tech 使用 Tiff in Tech 的 original sound 创作的 What is DNS?  DNS stands for Domain Name System. It's like the phone book of the internet. Just like you look up a person's name in a phone book to find their phone number, your computer uses DNS to look up a website's name to find its internet address (which is a number). When you type a website name like &quot;google.com&quot; into your browser, DNS is what helps your computer find the right server on the internet where that website is located, using the website's IP address. This process happens very quickly, allowing you to access websites easily just by knowing their names. #tech #techtok #techexplained " fetchpriority="auto" decoding="async" src="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/de5462e60cef4a4fbaeca184e71cceb3_1704845097?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=fbv%2By5r%2B5%2F1Djtt3AWfPCUn9MlQ%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=-" imagex-type="react" imagex-version="0.3.10" srcset="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/de5462e60cef4a4fbaeca184e71cceb3_1704845097?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=fbv%2By5r%2B5%2F1Djtt3AWfPCUn9MlQ%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 1x, https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/de5462e60cef4a4fbaeca184e71cceb3_1704845097?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=fbv%2By5r%2B5%2F1Djtt3AWfPCUn9MlQ%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 2x" style="position: absolute; inset: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0px; border: none; margin: auto; display: block; width: 0px; height: 0px; min-width: 100%; max-width: 100%; min-height: 100%; max-height: 100%;">

<img alt="Tiff in Tech 使用 Tiff in Tech 的 original sound 创作的 How does your cell phone magically connects you to anyone, anywhere? 1. Voice to Data: Your microphone captures your voice vibrations as analog signals. A microchip inside your phone converts these signals into a digital stream of numbers (think Morse code for sound!). Coding algorithms (codecs) like G.729 compress this data by removing redundancies, making it smaller for travel. 2. Data Takes Flight: The data transforms into a radio wave using modulation. Think of riding a sound wave (voice data) on top of a radio wave (carrier). Your phone's internal antenna blasts this modulated wave into the air. 3. The Cellular Symphony: Nearby cell towers receive the wave, extract the data (demodulation), and send it to the cellular network.  Smart computers called switching centers figure out where to send the data based on the recipient's number and network. The data jumps through the network like a digital hopscotch game, hopping between switching centers until it reaches the destination base station. 4. Data Back to Voice: The destination base station sends the data back out as a radio wave to the recipient's phone. Their phone's antenna receives the wave, extracts the data, and converts it back into electrical signals. Finally, a digital-to-analog converter transforms these signals back into sound waves, recreating your voice in their ear!" fetchpriority="auto" decoding="async" src="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/56eab529e38a47c6b4b7887e0187e129_1704666695?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=rW9mFZHhLRp0gMNGGs4zyOk4d%2BU%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=-" imagex-type="react" imagex-version="0.3.10" srcset="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/56eab529e38a47c6b4b7887e0187e129_1704666695?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=rW9mFZHhLRp0gMNGGs4zyOk4d%2BU%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 1x, https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/56eab529e38a47c6b4b7887e0187e129_1704666695?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=rW9mFZHhLRp0gMNGGs4zyOk4d%2BU%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 2x" style="position: absolute; inset: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0px; border: none; margin: auto; display: block; width: 0px; height: 0px; min-width: 100%; max-width: 100%; min-height: 100%; max-height: 100%;">

<img alt="Tiff in Tech 使用 Tiff in Tech 的 original sound 创作的 You’re not really deleting those files.  When you delete a file on your Mac, it doesn't vanish into thin air! It hangs out on your hard drive like a ghost hiding in the library stacks. Even though you can't see it on your desktop anymore, the actual file data is still there, chilling in unused space until something new writes over it.  This is why you can sometimes recover accidentally deleted files. Think of it like this: deleting a file is like removing the bookmark from your favorite book in the library catalog. The book itself is still on the shelf, just waiting for someone else to discover it. But if you really want that book gone for good, you need to shred it into tiny pieces, not just remove the bookmark.  #tech #techexpert #techexplained " fetchpriority="auto" decoding="async" src="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/oA1ZRbnTlEJ8E7B9wBmiYWeiIHBAQCAl4QfCDw?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=dsID0uV3FxPT48TZsoL9Cb6Sq5k%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=-" imagex-type="react" imagex-version="0.3.10" srcset="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/oA1ZRbnTlEJ8E7B9wBmiYWeiIHBAQCAl4QfCDw?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=dsID0uV3FxPT48TZsoL9Cb6Sq5k%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 1x, https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/oA1ZRbnTlEJ8E7B9wBmiYWeiIHBAQCAl4QfCDw?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=dsID0uV3FxPT48TZsoL9Cb6Sq5k%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 2x" style="position: absolute; inset: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0px; border: none; margin: auto; display: block; width: 0px; height: 0px; min-width: 100%; max-width: 100%; min-height: 100%; max-height: 100%;">

<img alt="Tiff in Tech 使用 Tiff in Tech 的 original sound 创作的 What happens when you type a url into the browser?  1. URL Parsing and DNS Lookup: The browser interprets the URL and uses DNS to convert the domain name into an IP address. 2. Connection Establishment: The browser establishes a TCP connection to the server (using TLS for HTTPS). 3. HTTP Request and Response: The browser sends an HTTP request to the server. The server processes this request and sends back a response. 4. Rendering the Web Page: The browser renders the page from the received HTML, CSS, and JavaScript. 5. JavaScript Execution: JavaScript runs, potentially modifying the page and making additional requests. 6. Connection Management: The browser manages the connection, keeping it open for further requests or closing it as needed. #tech #techeducation #techexplained " fetchpriority="auto" decoding="async" src="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/55a6d9f82a244de19d74a672cf522ecc_1704471097?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=qf0mR5MPHhk4RpamMO2GV4BtFOU%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=-" imagex-type="react" imagex-version="0.3.10" srcset="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/55a6d9f82a244de19d74a672cf522ecc_1704471097?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=qf0mR5MPHhk4RpamMO2GV4BtFOU%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 1x, https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/55a6d9f82a244de19d74a672cf522ecc_1704471097?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=qf0mR5MPHhk4RpamMO2GV4BtFOU%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 2x" style="position: absolute; inset: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0px; border: none; margin: auto; display: block; width: 0px; height: 0px; min-width: 100%; max-width: 100%; min-height: 100%; max-height: 100%;">

<img alt="Tiff in Tech 使用 Tiff in Tech 的 original sound 创作的 Why is there not always free Wi-Fi on planes?  I mean its 2024. Why is airline technology so far behind? The lack of free Wi-Fi on airplanes in 2024 is due to both financial incentives for airlines and technical limitations. To offer Wi-Fi, planes require antennas, a network modem, and wireless access points, with retrofitting existing aircraft being expensive and time-consuming.  Wi-Fi connectivity is achieved either through satellite antennas or air-to-ground (ATG) antennas. ATG antennas face challenges over large bodies of water, leading to reliance on satellite Wi-Fi, which uses orbiting satellites for data transmission, ensuring continuous connectivity. Airlines often use a hybrid of both systems. While charging for Wi-Fi does generate extra revenue for airlines, it also manages bandwidth limitations.  With potentially hundreds of passengers wanting to use the service, making it free would overwhelm the limited bandwidth, degrading the quality for everyone.  Hence, airlines charge for Wi-Fi to limit the number of users and maintain service quality.  #techtok #technology #techexplained " fetchpriority="auto" decoding="async" src="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/e66620df16584dfea3a6dfbcaec2b42f_1704312928?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=4HGvLPLkMIfleG%2BJNZ6%2BEqlRT6w%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=-" imagex-type="react" imagex-version="0.3.10" srcset="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/e66620df16584dfea3a6dfbcaec2b42f_1704312928?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=4HGvLPLkMIfleG%2BJNZ6%2BEqlRT6w%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 1x, https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/e66620df16584dfea3a6dfbcaec2b42f_1704312928?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=4HGvLPLkMIfleG%2BJNZ6%2BEqlRT6w%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 2x" style="position: absolute; inset: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0px; border: none; margin: auto; display: block; width: 0px; height: 0px; min-width: 100%; max-width: 100%; min-height: 100%; max-height: 100%;">

<img alt="Tiff in Tech 使用 Tiff in Tech 的 original sound 创作的 Who invented Wi-Fi? And how does it work? Hedy Lamarr was an Austrian-American actress and inventor who pioneered the technology that would one day form the basis for today's WiFi, GPS, and Bluetooth communication systems. While many people and organizations were involved, the person who contributed the most to the WiFi we know today is Vic Hayes. Many consider Hayes, who invented WiFi and call him “the father of WiFi.” Wi-Fi 6, also known as 802.11ax, is the latest generation of Wi-Fi technology, succeeding Wi-Fi 5 (802.11ac).  2.4 GHz is better for longer-range and compatibility but faces more interference and offers slower speeds. 5 GHz provides faster speeds and less interference but has a shorter range and requires more modern devices. 6 GHz (Wi-Fi 6E) offers the highest speeds and least interference but is limited in terms of device compatibility and range. #tech #techtok #techexplained " fetchpriority="auto" decoding="async" src="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/tos-maliva-p-0068/1a6a7a2c557447f689e5bb4e1898d64f_1703806900~tplv-dmt-logom:tos-useast2a-v-0068/oQI0HjELfHcDeFsbuuED2gAIS3CfAwhAwQAnEA.image?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=%2Bjy3f2%2Fr%2BFal6SI1%2B5b0N1MaTp8%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=-" imagex-type="react" imagex-version="0.3.10" srcset="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/tos-maliva-p-0068/1a6a7a2c557447f689e5bb4e1898d64f_1703806900~tplv-dmt-logom:tos-useast2a-v-0068/oQI0HjELfHcDeFsbuuED2gAIS3CfAwhAwQAnEA.image?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=%2Bjy3f2%2Fr%2BFal6SI1%2B5b0N1MaTp8%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 1x, https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/tos-maliva-p-0068/1a6a7a2c557447f689e5bb4e1898d64f_1703806900~tplv-dmt-logom:tos-useast2a-v-0068/oQI0HjELfHcDeFsbuuED2gAIS3CfAwhAwQAnEA.image?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=%2Bjy3f2%2Fr%2BFal6SI1%2B5b0N1MaTp8%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 2x" style="position: absolute; inset: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0px; border: none; margin: auto; display: block; width: 0px; height: 0px; min-width: 100%; max-width: 100%; min-height: 100%; max-height: 100%;">

<img alt="Tiff in Tech 使用 Tiff in Tech 的 original sound 创作的 What is binary code? Explained to a 5th grader 💡 Ever wondered how your phone understands your taps and swipes?  It all boils down to binary code, the language of computers! Imagine light switches: on is 1, off is 0. Binary code works the same way, using just these two digits to create instructions for everything your phone does. Want to see a cat video? ‍ That's a bunch of 1s and 0s telling your phone which pixels to light up on your screen. Sending a message? Yep, your words get translated into binary so they can zip through the internet. Playing a game? ️ Every button press, every jump, every explosion - all coded in 1s and 0s! Binary might seem like a secret language, but it's the invisible force powering our digital world. <img alt="Tiff in Tech 使用 Tiff in Tech 的 original sound 创作的 What is a JWT (JSON Web Token)? It is a sophisticated framework for authentication and information exchange. Encoded as a JSON object, it's structured in three parts: Header, Payload, and Signature. It's not just a token, it's a compact, URL-safe vessel carrying digitally signed data that can verify itself. Ideal for single sign-ons and bearer token patterns, JWTs are the linchpins of modern secure web services.  #TechDeepDive #CyberSecurity #JSONWebToken " fetchpriority="auto" decoding="async" src="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/oUaxRkiIEgoyLjufIoik359O9wEXACAbBA9IB3?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=tKHuIZ%2B7gDj5PyoPsZv%2Fwyf3NpM%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=-" imagex-type="react" imagex-version="0.3.10" srcset="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/oUaxRkiIEgoyLjufIoik359O9wEXACAbBA9IB3?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=tKHuIZ%2B7gDj5PyoPsZv%2Fwyf3NpM%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 1x, https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/oUaxRkiIEgoyLjufIoik359O9wEXACAbBA9IB3?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=tKHuIZ%2B7gDj5PyoPsZv%2Fwyf3NpM%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 2x" style="position: absolute; inset: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0px; border: none; margin: auto; display: block; width: 0px; height: 0px; min-width: 100%; max-width: 100%; min-height: 100%; max-height: 100%;">

<img alt="Tiff in Tech 使用 Tiff in Tech 的 original sound 创作的 🤖 Who wants to start building with natural language understanding (NLU) but doesn't know where to begin? You don't need to be a super coder! #ServiceNowPartner Let me show you how with @ServiceNow Generative AI Controller. ServiceNow is a leading platform that streamlines workflows and automates processes for enterprises. Their Generative AI Controller makes it easy to integrate AI into apps. I simply select the controller and choose the “generate content&quot; action. The controller handles connecting to the NLU model behind the scenes. It creates results for the end user with just a few clicks! No coding is required.   Save this for a quick way to get started with NLU in your apps today using ServiceNow's tools. <img alt="Tiff in Tech 使用 Chris Alan Lee 的 Swear By It 创作的 How to make some extra cash working in tech 👇 Freelance Coding: Whether it’s web development, app creation, or software solutions, your coding skills are in high demand. Tech Tutoring: Share your knowledge by tutoring coding, web development, or even basic computer skills.  Building and Selling Tech Tools: Develop useful tech tools or widgets and sell them online. Whether it's a productivity app, a unique WordPress plugin, or a new software tool, your innovation can turn into a steady income. Tech Blogging or Vlogging: Start a blog or YouTube channel focused on tech reviews, tutorials, or latest tech trends. Monetize through ads, sponsorships, or affiliate marketing. Participate in Paid Online Surveys or Beta Testing: Companies often pay for beta testing new products or for taking tech-focused surveys. Websites like UserTesting or BetaTesting can be a good start. Tech Consulting Services: If you have specialized knowledge, offer consulting services to businesses or startups. Hackathons:  Hackathon Aggregator Websites: Sites like Devpost, Hackathon.com, and Major League Hacking (MLH) are dedicated to listing various hackathons. These platforms allow you to filter events by location, date, and topic, making it easier to find one that suits your interests. University Websites: Many universities host hackathons and they often welcome participants from outside their student body. <img alt="Tiff in Tech 使用 Tiff in Tech 的 original sound 创作的 This is forever my roman empire.  What is quantum computing? 👇 Quantum computing is an advanced computing technology that leverages the principles of quantum mechanics, using qubits that can exist in multiple states simultaneously, unlike traditional bits in classical computers. This unique capability allows quantum computers to perform complex calculations, such as factoring large numbers, much faster than conventional computers. This speed poses a significant threat to current encryption methods, like RSA, which rely on the difficulty of these calculations for security. The potential of quantum computers to break these encryptions raises serious concerns about data security and privacy. In response, researchers are developing post-quantum cryptography, a new form of encryption believed to be secure against the capabilities of quantum computing, aiming to safeguard sensitive information in the impending quantum era. #tech #futuretech " fetchpriority="auto" decoding="async" src="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/40080f2810ac4fe2b9116ca99dd8282e_1700083223?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=qy12ep4c9v7I6W9nAdUit%2FXzXks%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=-" imagex-type="react" imagex-version="0.3.10" srcset="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/40080f2810ac4fe2b9116ca99dd8282e_1700083223?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=qy12ep4c9v7I6W9nAdUit%2FXzXks%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 1x, https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/40080f2810ac4fe2b9116ca99dd8282e_1700083223?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=qy12ep4c9v7I6W9nAdUit%2FXzXks%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 2x" style="position: absolute; inset: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0px; border: none; margin: auto; display: block; width: 0px; height: 0px; min-width: 100%; max-width: 100%; min-height: 100%; max-height: 100%;">

<img alt="Tiff in Tech 使用 Tiff in Tech 的 original sound 创作的 A DDoS attack is essentially a coordinated assault on the availability of a network service. It's executed by overwhelming the target - typically a web server - with a flood of internet traffic.  This traffic is not legitimate user requests; it's artificially generated and comes from many different sources, making it a &quot;distributed&quot; attack. Think of a server as a door through which your legitimate users need to pass. In a DDoS attack, this door is barraged by a huge crowd (traffic) that doesn't actually want to enter (non-legitimate requests); they just want to block the door so that the genuine users can't get through. From a technical perspective, this attack exploits the limited capacity of a network service. Servers have a finite amount of resources - like bandwidth, memory, and processing power. A DDoS attack saturates these resources. This means that real users' requests can't be processed, leading to service disruption or complete unavailability. #tech #techexpert #techexplained #coding #softwareengineer " fetchpriority="auto" decoding="async" src="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/okKKSjdVZCHIVALjtCfQCetCHnIygkeax8XGIK?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=QaQHEK5WzYQGgLPg6sn1NNDgvqI%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=-" imagex-type="react" imagex-version="0.3.10" srcset="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/okKKSjdVZCHIVALjtCfQCetCHnIygkeax8XGIK?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=QaQHEK5WzYQGgLPg6sn1NNDgvqI%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 1x, https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/okKKSjdVZCHIVALjtCfQCetCHnIygkeax8XGIK?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=QaQHEK5WzYQGgLPg6sn1NNDgvqI%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 2x" style="position: absolute; inset: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0px; border: none; margin: auto; display: block; width: 0px; height: 0px; min-width: 100%; max-width: 100%; min-height: 100%; max-height: 100%;">

LinkedIn’s Advanced AI Features: LinkedIn introduced new AI tools to streamline the job search process and enhance user interaction, particularly for premium subscribers. These features also aid in lead prospecting and account management, reflecting in a nearly 8% annual revenue surge as the platform hit 1 billion members. Amazon’s FTC Antitrust Saga: Amazon faces a massive antitrust lawsuit from the Federal Trade Commission (FTC), accusing the retail giant of consumer exploitation, particularly concerning Amazon Prime subscriptions. <img alt="Tiff in Tech 使用 Tiff in Tech 的 original sound 创作的 What is OAuth? OAuth (Open Authorization) is a standard for access delegation commonly used for token-based authentication and authorization. It allows third-party services to exchange your information without sharing your credentials. Here’s a simplified explanation with a real-world analogy: Imagine you have a safe deposit box at a bank, and the bank has a strict policy that only the owner of the safe deposit box (you) can access it with a key. Now, suppose you want your friend to retrieve some documents from your box. Authorization: Instead of giving your friend the key to your safe deposit box (which would be like sharing your password), you go to the bank and fill out some paperwork to give your friend permission to access your box. Token Exchange: The bank then gives your friend a one-time access token, a “visitor’s pass” of sorts. Access: Your friend uses this token to access your safe deposit box and retrieve the documents. They can’t do anything else, like removing other items or peeking into someone else’s box. Limited Scope: The permission you gave is for a specific task and does not grant additional rights beyond what was needed for the task. Revocation: After the task is complete, the bank revokes the one-time access token, and your friend can no longer access your box unless you authorize them again. #tech #techexplained #stem " fetchpriority="auto" decoding="async" src="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/tos-maliva-p-0068/d7c7f2dc5cb94adb9ac8f64345924a2f_1698014758~tplv-dmt-logom:tos-useast2a-v-0068/oMEAIJifaiVESWERhpNlWAFY4ACDyAQBAueF1C.image?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=eMYiNuEAv5RwYlynpr%2BpFPcJT04%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=-" imagex-type="react" imagex-version="0.3.10" srcset="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/tos-maliva-p-0068/d7c7f2dc5cb94adb9ac8f64345924a2f_1698014758~tplv-dmt-logom:tos-useast2a-v-0068/oMEAIJifaiVESWERhpNlWAFY4ACDyAQBAueF1C.image?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=eMYiNuEAv5RwYlynpr%2BpFPcJT04%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 1x, https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/tos-maliva-p-0068/d7c7f2dc5cb94adb9ac8f64345924a2f_1698014758~tplv-dmt-logom:tos-useast2a-v-0068/oMEAIJifaiVESWERhpNlWAFY4ACDyAQBAueF1C.image?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=eMYiNuEAv5RwYlynpr%2BpFPcJT04%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 2x" style="position: absolute; inset: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0px; border: none; margin: auto; display: block; width: 0px; height: 0px; min-width: 100%; max-width: 100%; min-height: 100%; max-height: 100%;">
https://www.tiktok.com/@tiffintech/video/7292880526849985798

<img alt="Tiff in Tech 使用 Tiff in Tech 的 original sound 创作的 Many people use the terms SDK and API interchangeably, but they actually refer to different things. An API (Application Programming Interface) allows two software programs to communicate with each other. It defines a set of functions and protocols for building software applications. For example, the Instagram API allows developers to access Instagram data and build apps that interact with the Instagram platform. An SDK (Software Development Kit) is a collection of tools that allows developers to build applications for a specific platform, like iOS or Android. The SDK includes API libraries/interfaces, documentation, code samples, processes etc. Basically, it provides everything a developer needs to start building apps for that platform. The Instagram SDK contains the Instagram API as well as libraries, code samples and guides specifically for building Instagram integrated apps for iOS, Android, Web etc. So the Instagram SDK is built on top of the Instagram API. In summary: API is the interface for communicating between software programs SDK is a complete package for building apps on a platform using its APIs So APIs provide the core communication while SDKs provide additional tools and libraries around those APIs for easier development. #tech #techexplained " fetchpriority="auto" decoding="async" src="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/tos-maliva-p-0068/oghItyImOMtF3gzNAoNDfLAkB0ECrcCqg1kyuC~tplv-dmt-logom:tos-useast2a-v-0068/o81kztOYCh1EIruVXAyofBWmEpI1AAEmAgFAD9.image?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=smnIZ4beYqPle6S8VSOTVNVvBvw%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=-" imagex-type="react" imagex-version="0.3.10" srcset="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/tos-maliva-p-0068/oghItyImOMtF3gzNAoNDfLAkB0ECrcCqg1kyuC~tplv-dmt-logom:tos-useast2a-v-0068/o81kztOYCh1EIruVXAyofBWmEpI1AAEmAgFAD9.image?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=smnIZ4beYqPle6S8VSOTVNVvBvw%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 1x, https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/tos-maliva-p-0068/oghItyImOMtF3gzNAoNDfLAkB0ECrcCqg1kyuC~tplv-dmt-logom:tos-useast2a-v-0068/o81kztOYCh1EIruVXAyofBWmEpI1AAEmAgFAD9.image?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=smnIZ4beYqPle6S8VSOTVNVvBvw%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 2x" style="position: absolute; inset: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0px; border: none; margin: auto; display: block; width: 0px; height: 0px; min-width: 100%; max-width: 100%; min-height: 100%; max-height: 100%;">

<img alt="Tiff in Tech 使用 Anderson .Paak 的 Make It Better (Instrumental) 创作的 Getting real-world coding experience (or other skills) can be tough when you're just starting out. But here's a tip - use your network of friends and family! Offer to build websites, apps, or automate tasks for them. Not only will you get invaluable practice, but you'll also have real projects for your portfolio. When it comes time for interviews, share how you took initiative and solved problems for people you know. Talk about how you had to scope out requirements, wear multiple hats, and manage projects end-to-end. These &quot;freelance&quot; experiences show you have initiative, hunger to learn, and ability to deliver. The bottom line is don't wait around for the perfect coding job to gain experience. Take advantage of opportunities in your existing network. Build real things for real people. Develop your skills. <img alt="Tiff in Tech 使用 Sabrina Carpenter 的 Feather - Sped Up 创作的 Get readh &amp; talk tech: startup vs. big tech edition. 👇 Base Salary: This is the regular, fixed amount of money you get paid by your employer for doing your job. It's usually expressed as an annual figure but paid out monthly or bi-weekly. Equity: Equity is like getting a tiny slice of the company pie. It represents a share of ownership in the company. If the company does well, the value of your slice can grow. Stock: Stock is a specific form of equity. It represents actual shares or pieces of the company that you own. If you have stock in a company, you own a part of that company, and you might make money if the company does well, usually through selling the stock at a higher price or through dividends (a share of the company's profits). In a nutshell, base salary is your regular pay, equity is a share of the ownership in the company, and stock is a specific form of that ownership. #tech #salary #TechTrends " fetchpriority="auto" decoding="async" src="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/tos-maliva-p-0068/b4a41cc1727c4aa09e1264cb945504db_1696203122~tplv-dmt-logom:tos-useast2a-v-0068/ow5e0ECMItRJAFAvhbR70QgSltAAqneTGADQAB.image?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=tMNXy2ZbWgYk0x%2FVNFQu2y3j6Aw%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=-" imagex-type="react" imagex-version="0.3.10" srcset="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/tos-maliva-p-0068/b4a41cc1727c4aa09e1264cb945504db_1696203122~tplv-dmt-logom:tos-useast2a-v-0068/ow5e0ECMItRJAFAvhbR70QgSltAAqneTGADQAB.image?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=tMNXy2ZbWgYk0x%2FVNFQu2y3j6Aw%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 1x, https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/tos-maliva-p-0068/b4a41cc1727c4aa09e1264cb945504db_1696203122~tplv-dmt-logom:tos-useast2a-v-0068/ow5e0ECMItRJAFAvhbR70QgSltAAqneTGADQAB.image?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=tMNXy2ZbWgYk0x%2FVNFQu2y3j6Aw%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 2x" style="position: absolute; inset: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0px; border: none; margin: auto; display: block; width: 0px; height: 0px; min-width: 100%; max-width: 100%; min-height: 100%; max-height: 100%;">

<img alt="Tiff in Tech 使用 sped up nightcore 的 Cola (Sped Up Version) 创作的 These are three simple things that can really improve the interviewers view on you during an interview.  1. Ask better questions like: ➡️What are some of the challenges facing the team/company right now? Demonstrates your interest in contributing to real issues. What are the next steps in the interview process? Shows planning and eagerness for the role. ➡️Is there room for professional development and growth at the company? Conveys your interest in advancing your skills. ➡️Does the company encourage further education and training? Shows desire to continue building your knowledge. 2. <img alt="Tiff in Tech 使用 Tiff in Tech 的 original sound 创作的 Have you ever wanted to get ahead by predicting the future?The famed sci-fi writer predicted tablets, smart homes, and space stations decades before they existed! 🤯 The remarkable Arthur C. Clarke was not only a brilliant science fiction writer, but a visionary futurist. Clarke foresaw many technological advances decades before they became reality. Among his forecasts that have come to pass are communications satellites, computer tablets, video calls, and space stations. He envisioned the internet long before it existed and described a worldwide communications network eerily similar to the real thing. Some of Clarke's predictions have yet to materialize but still could someday. He envisioned a future where we could grow or clone replacement organs, control the weather, harness the power of the sun, develop artificial intelligence superior to humans, and make contact with extraterrestrial life. Still super helpful to ensure you are meeting most of the keywords. Sometimes you might have that skill but it is just worded differently than in the resume! It is called Jobalytics! And it is free to use." fetchpriority="auto" decoding="async" src="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/oUIRkJkAtkny7be6nBEXUueupIBBqQbJD2EJg5?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=A0Qi9kOHeRyfQFmxd5eFgVy%2FC08%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=-" imagex-type="react" imagex-version="0.3.10" srcset="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/oUIRkJkAtkny7be6nBEXUueupIBBqQbJD2EJg5?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=A0Qi9kOHeRyfQFmxd5eFgVy%2FC08%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 1x, https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/oUIRkJkAtkny7be6nBEXUueupIBBqQbJD2EJg5?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=A0Qi9kOHeRyfQFmxd5eFgVy%2FC08%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 2x" style="position: absolute; inset: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0px; border: none; margin: auto; display: block; width: 0px; height: 0px; min-width: 100%; max-width: 100%; min-height: 100%; max-height: 100%;">

<img alt="Tiff in Tech 使用 Tiff in Tech 的 original sound 创作的 Microservices is an architectural approach in software development where an application is built as a collection of small, independent services.  Let's take an e-commerce platform as an example. Instead of one large application, it's broken down into separate services like User Management, Product Catalog, Shopping Cart, Payment, and Order Management.  Each service handles a specific business capability and communicates through APIs. With microservices, teams can work independently on each service, using different technologies if needed. They can scale and update services individually, resulting in better scalability, flexibility, and maintainability.  For example, during peak shopping seasons, the Product Catalog and Shopping Cart services can scale independently to handle increased traffic. However, it also introduces complexities like service communication and data consistency. Overall, microservices enable faster development, easier maintenance, and resilience by avoiding the dependence on a single large application. #tech #techexplained #learnontiktok #futuretech #techtok #stem " fetchpriority="auto" decoding="async" src="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/tos-maliva-p-0068/f2a58b6eb10c422b92ef6bb5b8f88e51_1685305054~tplv-dmt-logom:tos-useast2a-v-0068/1c3e9e7b3f4346d4ab634c3b669eb218.image?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=2HnobrPktCE2p5MEdsz87u9hS5w%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=-" imagex-type="react" imagex-version="0.3.10" srcset="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/tos-maliva-p-0068/f2a58b6eb10c422b92ef6bb5b8f88e51_1685305054~tplv-dmt-logom:tos-useast2a-v-0068/1c3e9e7b3f4346d4ab634c3b669eb218.image?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=2HnobrPktCE2p5MEdsz87u9hS5w%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 1x, https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/tos-maliva-p-0068/f2a58b6eb10c422b92ef6bb5b8f88e51_1685305054~tplv-dmt-logom:tos-useast2a-v-0068/1c3e9e7b3f4346d4ab634c3b669eb218.image?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=2HnobrPktCE2p5MEdsz87u9hS5w%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 2x" style="position: absolute; inset: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0px; border: none; margin: auto; display: block; width: 0px; height: 0px; min-width: 100%; max-width: 100%; min-height: 100%; max-height: 100%;">

<img alt="Tiff in Tech 使用 Tiff in Tech 的 original sound 创作的 What is a prompt engineer and how do you become one? Sharing some courses in the video as well!  Think of a &quot;prompt engineer&quot; like a teacher for artificial intelligence (AI). You know how when you're learning something new, a teacher might give you a problem or a question (a &quot;prompt&quot;) to help you understand? A prompt engineer does the same thing, but for AI. They design and create these prompts to teach the AI how to respond. For example, if you're using a voice assistant and you ask, &quot;What's the weather like today?&quot;, the AI knows how to respond correctly because a prompt engineer helped train it on this type of question. So essentially, a prompt engineer is someone who trains AI models to better understand and respond to different inputs or questions from users. They play a crucial role in making our interactions with AI more effective and natural. #promptengineering #chatgpt #ai #tech #techtok " fetchpriority="auto" decoding="async" src="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/tos-maliva-p-0068/o8GkFYEeTA3hBR8gQE8fcAJnhbAP4iADBEBFwI~tplv-dmt-logom:tos-useast2a-v-0068/6aa3cbd397324bd08b83a68f00d39306.image?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=kmZERybtKgQT%2FNe%2BfVF2XPLpkig%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=-" imagex-type="react" imagex-version="0.3.10" srcset="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/tos-maliva-p-0068/o8GkFYEeTA3hBR8gQE8fcAJnhbAP4iADBEBFwI~tplv-dmt-logom:tos-useast2a-v-0068/6aa3cbd397324bd08b83a68f00d39306.image?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=kmZERybtKgQT%2FNe%2BfVF2XPLpkig%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 1x, https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/tos-maliva-p-0068/o8GkFYEeTA3hBR8gQE8fcAJnhbAP4iADBEBFwI~tplv-dmt-logom:tos-useast2a-v-0068/6aa3cbd397324bd08b83a68f00d39306.image?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=kmZERybtKgQT%2FNe%2BfVF2XPLpkig%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 2x" style="position: absolute; inset: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0px; border: none; margin: auto; display: block; width: 0px; height: 0px; min-width: 100%; max-width: 100%; min-height: 100%; max-height: 100%;">

<img alt="Tiff in Tech 使用 Tiff in Tech 的 original sound 创作的 DevOps is about uniting development and IT operations teams for faster and more reliable software delivery. Imagine an e-commerce company. Before DevOps, the developers wrote code and then handed it off to operations for deployment. Issues often arose in this siloed approach, leading to blame games between the teams. With DevOps, these teams work together from the start, sharing responsibilities. Automation is a cornerstone, including automated testing and deployment, known as CI/CD. Monitoring tools quickly detect production issues, often resolving them before users notice. And crucially, feedback loops ensure that any problems found in production are swiftly communicated back to developers. So, DevOps speeds up development cycles, reduces deployment failures, quickens recovery from failure, and boosts team collaboration, allowing businesses to deliver improvements more rapidly and with less risk. #developer #tech #techexpert #techexplained " fetchpriority="auto" decoding="async" src="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/847f8d5d381a486bacd50ab2ab3e8d24_1684954855?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=SVCuOUjfh6m1aGbXdj7CZSrO27c%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=-" imagex-type="react" imagex-version="0.3.10" srcset="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/847f8d5d381a486bacd50ab2ab3e8d24_1684954855?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=SVCuOUjfh6m1aGbXdj7CZSrO27c%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 1x, https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/847f8d5d381a486bacd50ab2ab3e8d24_1684954855?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=SVCuOUjfh6m1aGbXdj7CZSrO27c%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 2x" style="position: absolute; inset: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0px; border: none; margin: auto; display: block; width: 0px; height: 0px; min-width: 100%; max-width: 100%; min-height: 100%; max-height: 100%;">

<img alt="Tiff in Tech 使用 Tiff in Tech 的 original sound 创作的 Save this for your next tech interview or when you are in a meeting and someone brings up CI/CD.  CI/CD stands for Continuous Integration and Continuous Deployment. It is a software development approach that focuses on frequent and automated code testing, building, and deployment to ensure high-quality and reliable software. In simpler terms, CI/CD is a process of continuously integrating changes to the codebase, automatically testing those changes, and then deploying them to production as soon as possible. For example, consider a software development team working on a mobile application. With CI/CD, every time a developer makes a change to the code, the change is automatically integrated with the rest of the codebase, and tests are run to ensure that the new code doesn't break any existing functionality. If the tests pass, the new code is automatically deployed to a staging environment where it can be further tested. If the code passes all tests and meets the requirements, it is then automatically deployed to production. #techtok #techexplained #stem  " fetchpriority="auto" decoding="async" src="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/oc1oIfAIkzy4GiCwvoYRAYCoEtZ2K9ghFEIvtB?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=H%2BwY6Fnsb0LTwtKHTUyf%2BoB1BEE%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=-" imagex-type="react" imagex-version="0.3.10" srcset="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/oc1oIfAIkzy4GiCwvoYRAYCoEtZ2K9ghFEIvtB?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=H%2BwY6Fnsb0LTwtKHTUyf%2BoB1BEE%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 1x, https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/oc1oIfAIkzy4GiCwvoYRAYCoEtZ2K9ghFEIvtB?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=H%2BwY6Fnsb0LTwtKHTUyf%2BoB1BEE%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 2x" style="position: absolute; inset: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0px; border: none; margin: auto; display: block; width: 0px; height: 0px; min-width: 100%; max-width: 100%; min-height: 100%; max-height: 100%;">

<img alt="Tiff in Tech 使用 dkj &amp; sped up nightcore 的 Aces (Sped Up Version) 创作的 Standford just released a large report on AI and here are some of the key takeaways:  AI systems are rapidly increasing their parameters is reflective of the increased complexity of the tasks they are being asked to perform, the greater availability of data, advancements in underlying hardware, and most importantly, the demonstrated performance of larger models AI research is growing exponentially. The number of AI repository publications grew almost 27 times in the past 12 years.  According to the statement, Minerva was trained using a compute power that was roughly nine times greater than that used for GPT-3, which was released in June 2022. Additionally, the compute power used for Minerva was roughly 1839 times greater than that used for GPT-2, which was released in February 2019. <img alt="Tiff in Tech 使用 Tiff in Tech 的 original sound 创作的 Save this for your next tech interview or when youre in a meeting and someone brings up proxy. The simple example in the video really helped me get it.  A proxy server is a tool that can be used to enhance security, bypass censorship, and improve performance. By acting as an intermediary between clients and the internet, a proxy server can mask a client's IP address from the destination server, making it difficult for the destination server to track or monitor activity. It can also be used to access content that may be restricted in certain locations by bypassing internet censorship. Additionally, proxies can help optimize online resources by caching frequently requested content and reducing load on the destination server. There are several types of proxy servers available including HTTP proxies, SOCKS proxies, transparent proxies and reverse proxies; each type has different features and applications. For example, HTTP proxies are often used to access websites while SOCKS proxies provide more versatile support for other network protocols. Transparent proxies help with routing requests while reverse proxies act as intermediaries between clients and web servers for enhanced security and performance optimization. #learnontiktok #howthingswork #techexplained #stem #stemtok " fetchpriority="auto" decoding="async" src="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/okR1HdBoIDIC9e7BMhkEZnIBLQjMJV1bQAbeJR?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=rGYm9C8ZYLGLs705kKQim9N364Y%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=-" imagex-type="react" imagex-version="0.3.10" srcset="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/okR1HdBoIDIC9e7BMhkEZnIBLQjMJV1bQAbeJR?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=rGYm9C8ZYLGLs705kKQim9N364Y%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 1x, https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/okR1HdBoIDIC9e7BMhkEZnIBLQjMJV1bQAbeJR?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=rGYm9C8ZYLGLs705kKQim9N364Y%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 2x" style="position: absolute; inset: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0px; border: none; margin: auto; display: block; width: 0px; height: 0px; min-width: 100%; max-width: 100%; min-height: 100%; max-height: 100%;">

<img alt="Tiff in Tech 使用 The King Khan &amp; BBQ Show 的 Love You So 创作的 A simple way to explain and understand what is DNS for a tech interview or if you hear it in a meeting.  Imagine you're trying to find the address of a house. You might use a map to locate the street, but you still need to know the house number to find the right place. Similarly, when you want to visit a website, you need to know its address or URL (Uniform Resource Locator). But instead of memorizing a bunch of numbers, we use domain names like google.  Now, how does your computer know where to find the website when you type in the domain name? That's where DNS (Domain Name System) comes in. DNS is like a phone book for the internet. When you type in a domain name, your computer sends a request to a DNS server, which looks up the IP (Internet Protocol) address associated with that domain name. An IP address is a unique numerical identifier that identifies the computer or server hosting the website. Once the DNS server finds the IP address, it sends it back to your computer, which can then connect to the web server hosting the website using that IP address. Think of it like looking up a phone number in a phone book and dialing it to connect to the person you want to talk to. DNS is important because it makes it easy for us to access websites and other internet resources without having to remember long strings of numbers. It also allows us to quickly switch between different servers or services that might be hosted on different IP addresses, while still using the same easy-to-remember domain name." fetchpriority="auto" decoding="async" src="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/owHISw9P7CeESAejTCuIcb9BlfIgg5bvnyLnDO?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=slygp391Nrml9xenBwjgIrZaE4E%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=-" imagex-type="react" imagex-version="0.3.10" srcset="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/owHISw9P7CeESAejTCuIcb9BlfIgg5bvnyLnDO?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=slygp391Nrml9xenBwjgIrZaE4E%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 1x, https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/owHISw9P7CeESAejTCuIcb9BlfIgg5bvnyLnDO?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=slygp391Nrml9xenBwjgIrZaE4E%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 2x" style="position: absolute; inset: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0px; border: none; margin: auto; display: block; width: 0px; height: 0px; min-width: 100%; max-width: 100%; min-height: 100%; max-height: 100%;">
https://www.tiktok.com/@tiffintech/video/7204596331191586075

<img alt="Tiff in Tech 使用 dtuhstuhd34 的 Ac r7sheed 创作的 4 jobs of the future that don’t exist yet 🤩 I love looking ahead of what’s (possibly) to come. It gets me really excited to be in tech during a time things are changing so quickly. A lot of these roles are already happening to certain degrees. What else would you add for jobs of the future? Space tour guide: Future lunar tourists will want to learn about space as they embark into it from a knowledgeable space tour guide! Life extension technologist: Even today, we’re always looking for ways to look and feel younger. In the future, you may actually be able to hire someone to prolong your youth. Chief Automation Officer: Automated systems from bill processing to mail sorting to automotive assembly are already becoming an important piece of most businesses. Soon there will be even more demand for tech-savvy employees to oversee and update these systems. <img alt="Tiff in Tech 使用 dtuhstuhd34 的 Ac r7sheed 创作的 Gone are the days where you can solely rely on technical skills without building soft skills. You absolutely need both (if you are a technical person). Here is some insight into the top soft skills to focus on.  1. Communication: Strong communication skills are essential for tech professionals as they need to be able to effectively express complex concepts and ideas in a way that is understandable to both technical and non-technical people. 2. Leadership: Tech professionals must have the ability to lead projects, develop innovative solutions, and motivate teams of individuals with different skill sets. 3. Problem Solving: In the tech industry, problem solving goes beyond coding; it involves being able to think creatively in order to overcome challenges while staying on track with deadlines and expectations from clients or other stakeholders.  4. Collaboration: Working together requires good interpersonal skills in order for everyone involved to function efficiently as a team toward achieving common goals. It also entails knowing how each member can best contribute their individual talents or strengths toward success.  5. Adaptability &amp; Flexibility: Technology changes rapidly so tech professionals must stay up-to-date with current trends and developments within their field which often necessitates quick adaptation of new information or processes into existing systems or products.. #learnontiktok #techcareer #stem #futuretech #career #techtok #softwareengineering " fetchpriority="auto" decoding="async" src="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/oEPB9CnV8eR36oXewRTMABVENndQgJEbQj8d6D?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=cBWtnimjp2kzlKo37K9KrqkjLm8%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=-" imagex-type="react" imagex-version="0.3.10" srcset="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/oEPB9CnV8eR36oXewRTMABVENndQgJEbQj8d6D?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=cBWtnimjp2kzlKo37K9KrqkjLm8%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 1x, https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/oEPB9CnV8eR36oXewRTMABVENndQgJEbQj8d6D?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=cBWtnimjp2kzlKo37K9KrqkjLm8%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 2x" style="position: absolute; inset: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0px; border: none; margin: auto; display: block; width: 0px; height: 0px; min-width: 100%; max-width: 100%; min-height: 100%; max-height: 100%;">

<img alt="Tiff in Tech 使用 Miley Cyrus 的 Flowers 创作的 There are many technical aspects as to what is takes to keep a massive app running (somewhat) smoothly!  Load balancing: distributing traffic evenly across multiple servers to prevent any one from becoming overwhelmed. Caching: storing frequently requested data temporarily in a cache to reduce server load and speed up responses. Database sharding: dividing large databases into smaller, more manageable parts to improve query performance and reduce load on the database. Content delivery networks (CDN): caching and serving static content such as images and videos closer to users to reduce network latency. Microservices architecture: breaking the application down into smaller, self-contained services to improve scalability and reliability. These and other techniques allow Instagram to handle high traffic while maintaining performance and availability. #learnontiktok #techexplained #tech #techtok " fetchpriority="auto" decoding="async" src="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/ogbjYDhABCBDZ4QAKgnRJjQp2IfOKNRHDe6EPD?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=2C9k1ylPM%2B0STwnb%2FlxKqAnlaFQ%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=-" imagex-type="react" imagex-version="0.3.10" srcset="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/ogbjYDhABCBDZ4QAKgnRJjQp2IfOKNRHDe6EPD?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=2C9k1ylPM%2B0STwnb%2FlxKqAnlaFQ%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 1x, https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/ogbjYDhABCBDZ4QAKgnRJjQp2IfOKNRHDe6EPD?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=2C9k1ylPM%2B0STwnb%2FlxKqAnlaFQ%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 2x" style="position: absolute; inset: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0px; border: none; margin: auto; display: block; width: 0px; height: 0px; min-width: 100%; max-width: 100%; min-height: 100%; max-height: 100%;">

https://www.tiktok.com/@tiffintech/video/7183052278104886534
<img alt="Tiff in Tech 使用 Heinz Kiessling 的 Blue Blood 创作的 How are passwords stored in databases? In order to store passwords in a database in a secure way, it is common to use a process called hashing. Hashing is a one-way function that takes an input (in this case, a password) and generates a fixed-size string of characters, known as a hash. The same input will always produce the same hash, but it is not possible to determine the original input from the hash. One important property of hashing is that it is computationally infeasible to generate the same hash for two different inputs. This means that if two different passwords are hashed, it is very unlikely that they will produce the same hash. In order to store a password in a database, the password is first hashed and the resulting hash is stored instead of the original password. When a user attempts to log in, the password they enter is hashed and the resulting hash is checked against the hash stored in the database. If the hashes match, the user is authenticated. However, there are certain types of attacks that can be used to try and determine the original password from a hash, such as a rainbow table attack. To make it more difficult for these types of attacks to be successful, it is common to use a technique called salting. Salting involves adding a random string of characters, known as a salt, to the password before hashing it. This means that even if two users have the same password, the hashes stored in the database will be different because the salt is different. This makes it much more difficult for an attacker to use a pre-computed hash table to try and determine the original passwords. In summary, to store and retrieve passwords in a database, the following process is used: ➡️ the password is combined with a random salt. ➡️ the combined password and salt are hashed. ➡️ the resulting hash and the salt are stored in the database. ➡️ when a user attempts to log in, their password is combined with the salt stored in the database and the resulting combined string is hashed. ➡️ the resulting hash is compared to the hash stored in the database. If the hashes match, the user is authenticated. #stem #learnontiktok #learntocode #tech #futureethis #edutok #techexplained " fetchpriority="auto" decoding="async" src="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/tos-maliva-p-0068/oYCag3NzkEJBIoxCYVqDi1y6vAAAkhj9fBGIIo~tplv-dmt-logom:tos-useast2a-v-0068/3228c547ee564445a015fe4e6b42d2b5.image?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=MbFH8UZep0s2gAvCVeDyfYWwPdg%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=-" imagex-type="react" imagex-version="0.3.10" srcset="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/tos-maliva-p-0068/oYCag3NzkEJBIoxCYVqDi1y6vAAAkhj9fBGIIo~tplv-dmt-logom:tos-useast2a-v-0068/3228c547ee564445a015fe4e6b42d2b5.image?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=MbFH8UZep0s2gAvCVeDyfYWwPdg%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 1x, https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/tos-maliva-p-0068/oYCag3NzkEJBIoxCYVqDi1y6vAAAkhj9fBGIIo~tplv-dmt-logom:tos-useast2a-v-0068/3228c547ee564445a015fe4e6b42d2b5.image?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=MbFH8UZep0s2gAvCVeDyfYWwPdg%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 2x" style="position: absolute; inset: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0px; border: none; margin: auto; display: block; width: 0px; height: 0px; min-width: 100%; max-width: 100%; min-height: 100%; max-height: 100%;">

<img alt="Tiff in Tech 使用 Heinz Kiessling 的 Blue Blood 创作的 How to explain what is DNS? 👇  To understand how DNS works, think of it like a phonebook or directory for the internet. When a user types in a domain name, their computer sends out a query through the DNS system looking up the associated IP address with that domain name. The DNS server then responds back with the corresponding IP address of where the website is located on the web server.  For example, when you type “www.example.com” into your browser bar, your computer will first send out a request to its local DNS cache for any cached information about that domain name; if none exists, it will then send out another query to its assigned DNS server asking for assistance in finding where this website is located on the web server so that content associated with it can be displayed to you on your screen. Once a response has been received from the DNS server, your computer will have access to all of the records associated with that particular website and it will be able to direct you to its content on your web browser window. " fetchpriority="auto" decoding="async" src="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/tos-maliva-p-0068/39e324b0cee0474b8a93229639a2a4ed_1672160970~tplv-dmt-logom:tos-useast2a-v-0068/afb516431e4c4b17b469c0c788ac8977.image?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=fA95wn9SkuU2iAQxZfUtyBQq2RE%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=-" imagex-type="react" imagex-version="0.3.10" srcset="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/tos-maliva-p-0068/39e324b0cee0474b8a93229639a2a4ed_1672160970~tplv-dmt-logom:tos-useast2a-v-0068/afb516431e4c4b17b469c0c788ac8977.image?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=fA95wn9SkuU2iAQxZfUtyBQq2RE%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 1x, https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/tos-maliva-p-0068/39e324b0cee0474b8a93229639a2a4ed_1672160970~tplv-dmt-logom:tos-useast2a-v-0068/afb516431e4c4b17b469c0c788ac8977.image?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=fA95wn9SkuU2iAQxZfUtyBQq2RE%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 2x" style="position: absolute; inset: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0px; border: none; margin: auto; display: block; width: 0px; height: 0px; min-width: 100%; max-width: 100%; min-height: 100%; max-height: 100%;">

<img alt="Tiff in Tech 使用 Heinz Kiessling 的 Blue Blood 创作的 Why Spotify Shuffle is Not Truly Random? Have you ever noticed that Spotify shuffle mode isn't really random? Yeah me too.  After using Spotify for many years myself and many others started realizing that some songs appear more than others.  But why does this happen? Shouldn't it be completely random? The short answer is no.  According to a former software Spotify engineer between 2012 and 2017 algorithm used to work perfectly random years ago. Thanks to a Fisher Yates algorithm. What is the Fisher Yates algorithm you ask? Take a look at this image. Which one seems more random? The first one right?  When thinking about a random algorithm the human brain tends to lean more towards the first one that it would make more random results than the second one.  However in the fisher yates algorithm they both equally could appear.  When the second lines appear they create a confusion among Spotify users who felt like finding the same songs in a row wasn't really random at all. So in 2014 Spotify actually changed its algorithm from being completely random to a new algorithm to appeal to the human brain.  For example if you had a play with with songs from Taylor Swift, Beyonce and say Drake, you sadly would never get 5 Beyonce songs in a row.  Although in a true random scenario the result would be entirely possible. But for the human brain it makes it think that the random algorithm is actually broken.  Our brains cannot process the concept of random very well and it's in our nature to look for patterns and ways to solve it.  #stem #techexplained #tech #technology #learntocode #futuretech #computerscience " fetchpriority="auto" decoding="async" src="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/tos-maliva-p-0068/okkzqzy0hOJAIJfoxj2AnoEtV9EIAoC1oEgpO2~tplv-dmt-logom:tos-useast2a-v-0068/2bc1ef1d00cd43b7a804488a8a14d94f.image?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=8VQsFow9dcDmggvOnsqGzCFI0ig%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=-" imagex-type="react" imagex-version="0.3.10" srcset="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/tos-maliva-p-0068/okkzqzy0hOJAIJfoxj2AnoEtV9EIAoC1oEgpO2~tplv-dmt-logom:tos-useast2a-v-0068/2bc1ef1d00cd43b7a804488a8a14d94f.image?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=8VQsFow9dcDmggvOnsqGzCFI0ig%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 1x, https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/tos-maliva-p-0068/okkzqzy0hOJAIJfoxj2AnoEtV9EIAoC1oEgpO2~tplv-dmt-logom:tos-useast2a-v-0068/2bc1ef1d00cd43b7a804488a8a14d94f.image?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=8VQsFow9dcDmggvOnsqGzCFI0ig%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 2x" style="position: absolute; inset: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0px; border: none; margin: auto; display: block; width: 0px; height: 0px; min-width: 100%; max-width: 100%; min-height: 100%; max-height: 100%;">

<img alt="Tiff in Tech 使用 walid 的 Nonsense by Sabrina carpenter 创作的 What is the difference between HTTP and HTTPS? Save this for your next tech interview 👇💡 HTTP is different than HTTPS: 1. HTTPS uses encryption, which means that your data is turned into a secret code before it's sent. This makes it harder for someone to steal your information. 2. HTTPS is more secure, which means it's less likely that someone will be able to hack into your website. 3. <img alt="Tiff in Tech 使用 Heinz Kiessling 的 Blue Blood 创作的 What is a firewall? Save this for your next tech interview 👇💡 I have a tech interview coming up and they're going to ask me about a firewall. How do I easily explain it?  A firewall is a network security device that analyzes traffic entering and leaving your network.  It allows or denies traffic based on a set of security rules Here's a real world example that will help you remember it.  The fencing around your house or property protects your home and keeps trespassers out.  Similarly firewalls are used to secure a computer network.  #tech #stem #techexpert #technology #techinterview #techinternship #learntocode #compsci " fetchpriority="auto" decoding="async" src="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/tos-maliva-p-0068/012ffc4742d946b5982cd2a28d779569_1671558982~tplv-dmt-logom:tos-useast2a-v-0068/7f6c158395ae4f94be0fd2abc6050a18.image?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=d62JuInvDY7821jViBgh7AUR1cE%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=-" imagex-type="react" imagex-version="0.3.10" srcset="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/tos-maliva-p-0068/012ffc4742d946b5982cd2a28d779569_1671558982~tplv-dmt-logom:tos-useast2a-v-0068/7f6c158395ae4f94be0fd2abc6050a18.image?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=d62JuInvDY7821jViBgh7AUR1cE%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 1x, https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/tos-maliva-p-0068/012ffc4742d946b5982cd2a28d779569_1671558982~tplv-dmt-logom:tos-useast2a-v-0068/7f6c158395ae4f94be0fd2abc6050a18.image?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=d62JuInvDY7821jViBgh7AUR1cE%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 2x" style="position: absolute; inset: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0px; border: none; margin: auto; display: block; width: 0px; height: 0px; min-width: 100%; max-width: 100%; min-height: 100%; max-height: 100%;">

<img alt="Tiff in Tech 使用 The King Khan &amp; BBQ Show 的 Love You So 创作的 Single sign-on is a process that lets you use one set of login information (like a password) to access multiple websites or services.  One example of single sign-on (SSO) is the use of an employee's login credentials for their corporate intranet to access their office applications, such as cloud storage or email. This allows the user to log in with just one set of credentials – a username and password – and receive access to all authorized applications across the organization.   #stem #tech #techtok #techexplained #learntocode #devops #futurejobs #DoTheSmartThings " fetchpriority="auto" decoding="async" src="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/oseRFQAkLgAfJ4V5Bkf4D2EwkAHhFEP5OQeGv4?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=wANEjDWowkiJY8NDuYABHzCUWaQ%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=-" imagex-type="react" imagex-version="0.3.10" srcset="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/oseRFQAkLgAfJ4V5Bkf4D2EwkAHhFEP5OQeGv4?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=wANEjDWowkiJY8NDuYABHzCUWaQ%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 1x, https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/oseRFQAkLgAfJ4V5Bkf4D2EwkAHhFEP5OQeGv4?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=wANEjDWowkiJY8NDuYABHzCUWaQ%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 2x" style="position: absolute; inset: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0px; border: none; margin: auto; display: block; width: 0px; height: 0px; min-width: 100%; max-width: 100%; min-height: 100%; max-height: 100%;">

<img alt="Tiff in Tech 使用 Heinz Kiessling 的 Blue Blood 创作的 How to explain HTTP request in a tech interview? What are HTTP requests?   HTTP/1 to HTTP/2 to HTTP/3. What do these numbers mean and why should you care? In the world of technology, it is important to stay ahead of the curve.  HTTP/1 was the first http protocol released in the 90s. It was designed to send and receive webpages from a server. This protocol worked by establishing separate data connections for each of the http requests sent by the client or browser. Because of this, http/1 was slow and prone to latency issues.  HTTP 1.1 came soon after  It introduced a keep alive mechanism   In 2015, http/2 was released as an upgrade to http/1, designed to improve performance and reduce latency. This solved the problem of http/1's slow speed and made webpages load faster. It also introduced header compression, allowing http headers to be compressed and reducing the amount of data sent over the connection.  The latest http protocol, http/3, was released in 2018. http/3 can transmit data up to three times faster than http/2, as well as being more secure due to its encryption. http/3 also supports multiplexing and header compression, building upon the features of http/2.  #stem #tech #techexplained #compsci #coding #techeducation #womeninstem " fetchpriority="auto" decoding="async" src="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/7d8ad001a3a84beb922f68f96f99e294_1669232293?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=jGjz4KHb7Anj0BcE6Y9%2FNZody6o%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=-" imagex-type="react" imagex-version="0.3.10" srcset="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/7d8ad001a3a84beb922f68f96f99e294_1669232293?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=jGjz4KHb7Anj0BcE6Y9%2FNZody6o%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 1x, https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/7d8ad001a3a84beb922f68f96f99e294_1669232293?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=jGjz4KHb7Anj0BcE6Y9%2FNZody6o%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 2x" style="position: absolute; inset: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0px; border: none; margin: auto; display: block; width: 0px; height: 0px; min-width: 100%; max-width: 100%; min-height: 100%; max-height: 100%;">

<img alt="Tiff in Tech 使用 Echosmith 的 Cool Kids (our sped up version) 创作的 What is the difference between SQL and NoSQL and which one to learn first? 💡  SQL databases are primarily called as Relational Databases (RDBMS); whereas NoSQL database are primarily called as non-relational. <img alt="Tiff in Tech 使用 Funk Tribu 的 Phonky Tribu 创作的 When I first entered the tech world there were ALOT of phrases I was confused about 🤣 here are some of them!   Yoda Conditions: When a programmer writes the conditions for a piece of code in the opposite order for which you would expect to normally read them. (Instead of saying if(variable == constant), the code says if(constant == variable).)  Heisenbug: A play on &quot;Heisenberg,&quot; a principle in quantum mechanics, a Heisenbug is a bug that disappears or alters its characteristics when an attempt is made to study it.  Jenga code: The whole program collapses once you alter a block of code.  Common law feature: A bug that has existed for so long that it is considered a feature.  #stem #tech #techtoktips " fetchpriority="auto" decoding="async" src="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/1033532a43ff4638aaf12c3a9be419b8?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=KndsQbn%2FyHpfTd78N%2BV4GYPepaM%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=-" imagex-type="react" imagex-version="0.3.10" srcset="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/1033532a43ff4638aaf12c3a9be419b8?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=KndsQbn%2FyHpfTd78N%2BV4GYPepaM%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 1x, https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/1033532a43ff4638aaf12c3a9be419b8?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=KndsQbn%2FyHpfTd78N%2BV4GYPepaM%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 2x" style="position: absolute; inset: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0px; border: none; margin: auto; display: block; width: 0px; height: 0px; min-width: 100%; max-width: 100%; min-height: 100%; max-height: 100%;">
